WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.750 --> 00:00:06.824
Subtitles downloaded from Podnapisi.NET

2
00:00:10.150 --> 00:00:15.355
THE BAND WAGON
片名：花車


3
00:01:38.313 --> 00:01:42.265
Yes, ladies and gentlemen,
we are in luck today here in Los Angeles.
是的，各位女士先生我們有幸齊聚洛杉磯


4
00:01:42.569 --> 00:01:44.940
Through the years,
the Bullwinkle Galleries...
這麼多年來布威克藝廊


5
00:01:45.029 --> 00:01:46.737
have brought up for auction...
我們為


6
00:01:46.823 --> 00:01:51.032
many collections of the personal effects
of your famous movie stars.
許多知名電影明星個人收藏品的拍賣會


7
00:01:51.117 --> 00:01:52.195
AUCTION SALE
舉辦拍賣


8
00:01:52.284 --> 00:01:55.535
But today is indeed a red-letter day.
但是今天真的非常特別


9
00:01:55.622 --> 00:01:58.492
The personal effects of Tony Hunter!
東尼杭特的個人收藏!


10
00:01:58.875 --> 00:02:00.037
Lot 94.
第94件!


11
00:02:00.209 --> 00:02:04.077
Ladies and gentlemen,
let's start out with Lot 94.
各位女士先生我們從第94件開始


12
00:02:04.714 --> 00:02:09.174
Some of the potpourri
of Mr. Hunter's own personal costumes...
些戲服是杭特先生


13
00:02:09.551 --> 00:02:13.134
that he used in his famous
dancing-singing pictures.
在他成名的歌舞片中所穿的


14
00:02:13.347 --> 00:02:16.466
Remember this?
Perhaps the most famous top hat...
最出名的禮帽和手杖


15
00:02:16.558 --> 00:02:18.467
and stick of our generation.
記得這個嗎?可能是我們這一代


16
00:02:18.560 --> 00:02:22.474
<i>Yes, the one he used
in Swinging Down to Panama...</i>
對，在電影《一路跳到巴拿馬》


17
00:02:22.564 --> 00:02:24.686
and all his other famous pictures.
以及其它所有知名電影都出現過


18
00:02:25.066 --> 00:02:28.683
Let's start with $5. Do I hear $5?
我們從5塊錢起價，有人出5塊嗎?


19
00:02:29.236 --> 00:02:31.145
It's worth a lot more.
這可是值更多錢


20
00:02:31.572 --> 00:02:33.898
All right. Let's start with $2.
好，我們從2塊起價


21
00:02:34.451 --> 00:02:37.486
Well? 50 cents?
沒有人?那5O分呢?


22
00:02:39.539 --> 00:02:40.819
Anything?
隨便開價?


23
00:02:49.423 --> 00:02:52.756
Just one more for the road.
About 20 minutes to New York.
再喝一杯就好了2O分鐘後就到紐約了


24
00:02:52.842 --> 00:02:54.171
Bottoms up.
乾杯


25
00:02:57.471 --> 00:03:00.306
- So you're from California?
- That's right. Sunny Cal.
- 你來自加州?
- 對，陽光加州


26
00:03:00.390 --> 00:03:02.798
- Sunny Cal?
- Yeah. Sunny Cal.
- 陽光加州?
- 對，陽光加州


27
00:03:03.101 --> 00:03:06.801
Say, you're from Sunny Cal. I bet
you know a lot of movie stars out there.
既然你來自陽光加州你一定認識很多電影明星


28
00:03:06.896 --> 00:03:09.138
I got to confess. I'm just like you and me.
說實在的，我跟大家一樣


29
00:03:09.232 --> 00:03:11.641
Only get to see them in the movies.
只從電影認識他們


30
00:03:11.736 --> 00:03:14.357
But I read about them.
I know all about them.
但是我看他們的相關報導
我很瞭解他們


31
00:03:15.530 --> 00:03:18.485
Boy, I'd sure like to meet
that Ava Gardner.
老天，我很想認識愛娃蓋勒


32
00:03:18.866 --> 00:03:21.488
- You're a little late. She's married.
- Yeah.
你晚了一步，她結婚了—對


33
00:03:21.995 --> 00:03:23.905
- You know this one?
- Who's that?
你認識他嗎?
他是誰?


34
00:03:23.998 --> 00:03:27.200
- Tony Hunter.
- Oh, him. The singing-dancing fella.
東尼杭特
哦，他，演歌舞片的那個


35
00:03:27.459 --> 00:03:31.539
My wife used to go see all his pictures.
Almost broke up our home.
我太太從前都要看他每一部電影
幾乎毀了我們的婚姻


36
00:03:31.630 --> 00:03:33.703
"Tony Hunter! Tony Hunter!"
東尼杭特!東尼杭特!


37
00:03:34.213 --> 00:03:36.123
He was good 12 or 15 years ago...
他在l2到l5年前很紅


38
00:03:36.216 --> 00:03:38.505
but the columnists out there
say he's through.
但是加州的專欄作家說他過氣了


39
00:03:39.344 --> 00:03:42.962
Through? He's washed up.
Hasn't made a picture in three years.
過氣?
他被淘汰了3年沒拍電影了


40
00:03:43.056 --> 00:03:46.140
- Did you say something, mister?
- I said I agreed with you.
先生，你是不是說了什麼?
我說我同意


41
00:03:46.226 --> 00:03:47.804
That Tony Hunter's a has-been.
那個東尼杭特不紅了


42
00:03:47.893 --> 00:03:49.637
- Got a match?
- Yeah.
有火柴嗎？
有


43
00:03:49.729 --> 00:03:53.857
I wouldn't go to see him
if they gave away $5 bills with the ticket.
就算他們送我票再給我5塊錢
要我去看他的電影，我也不幹


44
00:03:54.568 --> 00:03:55.682
Yeah.
對


45
00:03:57.862 --> 00:03:59.772
We should be pulling...
我們應該


46
00:04:00.115 --> 00:04:04.777
The funny thing about what you're saying,
boys, is that it's absolutely true.
你剛剛說的很有意思
老天，說得一點都沒錯


47
00:04:05.078 --> 00:04:07.484
Here. Have an exploding cigar.
來，來根道具雪茄


48
00:04:23.386 --> 00:04:25.710
- This the last of the bags, Mr. Hunter?
- Yeah.
杭特先生，這是最後一件?
對


49
00:04:25.804 --> 00:04:28.722
Say, porter, could you see that
they get put in a taxi...
小弟，你可以把行李裝到計程車上


50
00:04:28.808 --> 00:04:32.887
- and taken up to the Plaza Hotel?
- Yes, sir. Thank you, sir.
然後送到廣場旅館?
是的，先生，謝謝你


51
00:04:33.896 --> 00:04:35.520
Everybody's getting off, sir.
先生，大家都下車了


52
00:04:35.606 --> 00:04:38.973
If you don't mind,
I'll just sit for a minute or two.
如果你不介意，我只要再坐l、2分鐘


53
00:04:39.066 --> 00:04:42.270
You couldn't just make up my berth
for the night here, could you?
今晚你不能再這裏為我弄睡鋪，是嗎?


54
00:04:42.362 --> 00:04:44.485
No, sir. I couldn't do that.
先生，不行，我不能那樣做


55
00:04:56.167 --> 00:04:58.954
There's a mob of reporters
and photographers out there.
外面有一大票記者和攝影師


56
00:04:59.045 --> 00:05:02.247
Yep. There must be some big shot aboard.
Maybe the President.
對，車上一定有什麼大人物
說不定是總統


57
00:05:02.339 --> 00:05:05.459
No, too many for that.
Probably a movie star.
不，總統不會吸引這麼多媒體
可能是電影明星


58
00:05:11.932 --> 00:05:14.504
- Hi, fellas.
- Tony Hunter! Hello, Mr. Hunter!
嗨，大夥兒
東尼杭特!嗨，杭特先生


59
00:05:14.850 --> 00:05:17.423
Thanks for the red-carpet bit.
I didn't expect it.
沒想到你們特別趕來迎接我，謝謝


60
00:05:17.519 --> 00:05:20.853
- What brings you to New York?
- Just fooling around and relaxing.
你到紐約來幹嘛?
只是看一看、放鬆一下


61
00:05:20.940 --> 00:05:23.181
- Between pictures, Tony?
- In a manner of speaking.
東尼，趁拍片的空檔?
說起來


62
00:05:23.275 --> 00:05:26.277
<i>Didn't I read something in Variety
about you going into a show?</i>
我在《浮華世界》看到你
是不是準備參加一個演出?


63
00:05:26.362 --> 00:05:29.895
Lily and Les Marton had something
planned for me. I haven't decided yet.
莉莉和李斯莫頓為我
籌劃了一齣戲找還沒決定


64
00:05:29.989 --> 00:05:34.035
I haven't been on the stage in a long time.
And you get into a different medium.
我很久沒演舞台劇了
媒體對待也不同了


65
00:05:34.120 --> 00:05:36.159
- What it actually is...
- Here she is, fellas!
事實上是…
大夥兒，她來了


66
00:05:36.247 --> 00:05:38.239
- Excuse me, Mr. Hunter.
- See you later, Tony.
杭特先生，失陪
東尼，等會見


67
00:05:38.332 --> 00:05:39.363
Hi, Miss Gardner.
蓋勒小姐


68
00:05:39.458 --> 00:05:41.866
Miss Gardner, hold it, please?
Smile pretty. Thanks.
蓋勒小姐，拜託不要動?
笑得真漂亮，謝謝


69
00:05:41.960 --> 00:05:45.626
- How long you going to be in town?
- I have no definite plans. I thought...
你要在這裏待多久?
我沒有明確的計劃，我想


70
00:05:45.714 --> 00:05:48.204
Tony! I had no idea you were on the train.
東尼!我不知道你也在這列火車上


71
00:05:48.299 --> 00:05:50.338
This is a surprise.
You going to be here long?
真是意外，
你會停留很久嗎?


72
00:05:50.426 --> 00:05:52.750
- Perhaps a week or two...
- Excuse me, Miss Gardner.
也許一、兩個星期
對不起，蓋勒小姐


73
00:05:52.844 --> 00:05:55.679
Could the boys get one more shot of you
coming out the door?
可以讓他們再拍一張
你下車的照片?


74
00:05:55.764 --> 00:05:58.434
Honestly, isn't all this stuff an awful bore?
說實話，這些東西是不是非常無聊?


75
00:05:58.517 --> 00:06:00.593
- Good to see you, Tony.
- It's nice to see you.
東尼，見到你真好
見到你真好


76
00:06:00.686 --> 00:06:04.552
By the door, please, Miss Gardner.
Once more! Here we go! Thank you.
蓋勒小姐，請站在門邊再一張!
好了!謝謝


77
00:06:04.647 --> 00:06:08.597
Miss Gardner, my paper would like
to do a Sunday feature on you.
蓋勒小姐，我們報社
星期天想為你做一個專訪


78
00:06:09.986 --> 00:06:13.486
Those poor movie stars. People just
won't let them alone, will they?
那些可憐的電影明星
大家就是纏著他們不放，不是嗎?


79
00:06:13.574 --> 00:06:16.029
No. I don't know how they stand it.
不，我不知道他們怎麼受得了


80
00:06:19.580 --> 00:06:23.991
<i>I'll go my way by myself</i>
我要走自己的路


81
00:06:25.334 --> 00:06:28.916
<i>like walking under the clouds</i>
就像漫步雲端


82
00:06:30.922 --> 00:06:35.002
<i>I'll go my way by myself</i>
我要走自己的路


83
00:06:36.094 --> 00:06:39.677
<i>all alone in a crowd</i>
沒有人圍觀


84
00:06:41.850 --> 00:06:45.847
<i>I'll try to apply myself</i>
我要讓自己專注


85
00:06:47.063 --> 00:06:50.348
<i>and teach my heart how to sing</i>
讓我的心如何歌唱


86
00:06:52.610 --> 00:06:56.523
<i>I'll go my way by myself</i>
我要走自己的路


87
00:06:57.572 --> 00:07:01.237
<i>like a bird on the wing</i>
就像烏展翅翱翔


88
00:07:03.246 --> 00:07:07.029
<i>I'll face the unknown</i>
我要面對未知


89
00:07:08.333 --> 00:07:12.543
<i>I'll build a world of my own</i>
我一切要靠自己


90
00:07:13.754 --> 00:07:18.216
<i>No one knows better than I, myself</i>
沒有比我更清楚自己


91
00:07:18.926 --> 00:07:24.087
<i>I'm by myself alone</i>
我要靠自己


92
00:07:41.907 --> 00:07:44.824
Tony Hunter! There's Tony Hunter!
東尼杭特!他是東尼杭特!


93
00:07:45.743 --> 00:07:50.321
HI TONY - WELCOME TONY
TONY HUNTER FAN CLUB
嗨，東尼
歡迎東尼東尼杭特影迷俱樂部


94
00:07:52.666 --> 00:07:54.908
Did you kids paint those signs just for me?
你們專門為我畫的嗎?真可愛


95
00:07:55.002 --> 00:07:57.078
That's cute. Piggy.
豬仔，真可愛


96
00:07:58.297 --> 00:07:59.922
Let's get rid of this stuff.
把這些東西放下


97
00:08:00.631 --> 00:08:02.919
This is the biggest surprise I've had.
這是我有生以來最大的驚喜


98
00:08:07.180 --> 00:08:10.928
- Mister, can I have your autograph?
- You certainly can, gal, come here!
先生，幫我簽名好嗎?
當然好，過來!


99
00:08:11.016 --> 00:08:12.427
That's my wife.
Let go.
那是我太太
走開吧


100
00:08:12.518 --> 00:08:14.890
Don't worry.
I'll get around to you in a minute.
別擔心，
我等一下就還你


101
00:08:14.979 --> 00:08:16.935
- Who's he?
- Never saw him before in my life.
他是誰?
從來沒見過他


102
00:08:17.022 --> 00:08:19.893
- Hello, piggy!
- Hello, yourself, you two-headed creep!
嗨，豬仔!
嗨，你在叫你自己吧


103
00:08:19.983 --> 00:08:21.691
Why didn't you say
when you were coming?
你為什麼不說
幾時要來?


104
00:08:21.777 --> 00:08:23.058
We had to ask your agent.
我們還問你經紀人


105
00:08:23.154 --> 00:08:26.108
- Why didn't you send us a wire?
- I wanted to sneak in quietly.
為什麼不發個電報給我們?
我要悄悄地來


106
00:08:26.198 --> 00:08:30.279
Believe me, I didn't have any trouble.
I want to see if you've changed in a year.
相信我，一點麻煩都沒遇上
我要看看你們兩個一年來有沒有變


107
00:08:30.369 --> 00:08:33.786
No, Les, you haven't changed a bit.
You look desperately ill, as usual.
不，李斯，你一點都沒變跟平常一樣
一副病得很重的樣子


108
00:08:33.873 --> 00:08:36.113
- What'd you have to say that for?
- Just kidding.
你為什麼這樣說?
只是開玩笑


109
00:08:36.207 --> 00:08:37.701
I've been feeling terrible all day.
我一整天都不對勁


110
00:08:37.792 --> 00:08:42.085
Kind of faint, light-headed,
a lot of pressure here, queasy inside...
有點昏昏沉沉、頭重腳輕這裏壓迫感很大、
很想吐、


111
00:08:42.171 --> 00:08:43.713
- my pulse...
- You look great.
我的脈搏
你很好


112
00:08:43.797 --> 00:08:47.463
As for you, that New York pallor
is like a breath of fresh air.
而你紐約式的白皙
使人耳目一新


113
00:08:47.551 --> 00:08:51.762
You're too pretty to be a successful writer
and much too pretty to be married to that.
憑你的美貌，不該只是個成功的作家
更不應該嫁給他


114
00:08:51.847 --> 00:08:54.052
That's the prettiest compliment
I've had all day!
這是我一整天
聽到最棒的讚美!


115
00:08:54.140 --> 00:08:56.927
Come on, you two-headed lovebirds,
there's work to be done!
來，你們兩個互相愛慕的人
我們有正事要辦!


116
00:08:57.018 --> 00:09:00.517
- Now I have here a script of a show!
- Les, you didn't bring it.
我有一齣戲的劇本
你還真帶來了!


117
00:09:00.605 --> 00:09:02.977
It's great. It's the best thing
we've ever written.
非常棒，是我們寫過
最好的劇本


118
00:09:03.066 --> 00:09:05.474
Take it, boy. Smell it!
You can tell it's good.
給你，聞聞看!你就知道有多好


119
00:09:05.569 --> 00:09:08.521
There's a great part in it for you,
nice little parts for us.
你的戲份很重，我們只有一點點


120
00:09:08.612 --> 00:09:11.400
Wait. This boy must be starving.
Let's take him to Sardi's.
等等，他一定餓壞了我們帶他去莎蒂吃飯


121
00:09:16.495 --> 00:09:18.488
Only two blocks more, then Sardi's.
只要走兩條街就是莎蒂


122
00:09:18.581 --> 00:09:21.582
- Shall we tell him, Lil, the big surprise?
- You tell him, Les.
莉莉，我們該告訴他大驚喜嗎?
李斯，你告訴他


123
00:09:21.666 --> 00:09:23.743
Who do you think is going to do the show?
你認為誰該導這齣戲?


124
00:09:23.836 --> 00:09:27.964
Only the greatest director /producer
in town, Jeffrey Cordova.
紐約最棒的導演兼製片傑佛瑞可多瓦


125
00:09:28.173 --> 00:09:30.081
- Who?
- Jeff Cordova.
誰?
傑夫可多瓦


126
00:09:30.174 --> 00:09:32.962
We're meeting him tonight, backstage,
right after the show.
今晚表演結束時我們要在後台跟他碰面


127
00:09:33.052 --> 00:09:35.674
- What did you say his name was?
- Jeffrey Cordova!
你說他叫什麼名字?
傑佛瑞可多瓦!


128
00:09:35.764 --> 00:09:36.962
You're not serious.
你不是當真吧


129
00:09:37.057 --> 00:09:39.299
I don't think he ever heard of this fella.
我從沒聽過他這個人的名字


130
00:09:39.392 --> 00:09:42.392
What's the matter? Don't you
get newspapers back in California?
怎麼啦?
加州沒有報紙嗎?


131
00:09:42.477 --> 00:09:44.932
<i>This genius directed Man in a Mousetrap...</i>
這個天才導演過《困在補鼠器的人》


132
00:09:45.020 --> 00:09:49.518
<i>The Lost Nymph, and did them both
while starring in Oedipus Rex.</i>
《消失的僊女》而且同時演出《伊底帕斯王》


133
00:09:49.610 --> 00:09:52.527
He's got three hits running,
and he's starring in one of them.
他最近同時推出三齣
很轟動的戲他參加演其中一齣


134
00:09:52.613 --> 00:09:53.644
Only one?
才一齣?


135
00:09:53.739 --> 00:09:57.784
This fella's fabulous, phenomenal,
fantastic! He can do anything.
這是個不凡、驚人、
非常棒的人才他什麼都會


136
00:09:57.869 --> 00:09:59.658
Has he ever directed a musical?
他有沒有導過音樂劇?


137
00:09:59.744 --> 00:10:01.820
What's the difference? He can do anything.
有什麼差別?他什麼都會


138
00:10:01.913 --> 00:10:04.950
He's theatre.
He's a new kind of theatre man, Tony.
