277
00:20:58.905 --> 00:21:00.815
that's all I had to know.
我什麼都不再多問


278
00:21:00.991 --> 00:21:04.657
I'm dropping every other project,
and there are plenty, believe me.
我放棄了很多劇本相信我，非常多


279
00:21:05.497 --> 00:21:09.909
That's wonderful, Mr. Cordova,
but all this... The classics...
太好了，可多瓦先生但是這整個古典劇…


280
00:21:10.542 --> 00:21:14.622
- Do you really want to do a musical?
- Musical, musical!
你真的要拍音樂劇?
音樂劇，音樂劇!


281
00:21:14.713 --> 00:21:18.628
I'm sick of these artificial barriers
between the musical and the drama.
我受夠了界於音樂劇和戲劇間的虛偽屏障


282
00:21:18.968 --> 00:21:22.632
In my mind, there is no difference
between the magic rhythms...
在我心裏，永恆的莎士比亞創造的奇妙韻律…


283
00:21:22.721 --> 00:21:26.506
of Bill Shakespeare's immortal verse
and the magic rhythms...
和不朽的比爾羅賓森舞出的神奇節奏…


284
00:21:26.601 --> 00:21:29.005
of Bill Robinson's immortal feet.
是一樣的


285
00:21:29.684 --> 00:21:32.306
Hal, write that down.
I'll use it at Princeton.
哈爾，記下來，我要用在普林斯頓大學的演說


286
00:21:32.396 --> 00:21:34.305
It's already down. You used it last week.
已經寫下來了，你上禮拜用過


287
00:21:34.398 --> 00:21:37.066
I tell you, if it moves you,
if it stimulates you...
我告訴你，能讓你感動的能刺激你的…


288
00:21:37.150 --> 00:21:39.309
if it entertains you, it's theatre.
能娛樂你的，就是劇場


289
00:21:39.445 --> 00:21:42.730
When the right combination gets together
and it spells theatre...
當所有對的東西集合在一起形成劇場…


290
00:21:42.822 --> 00:21:46.025
I got to be right in there up to my armpits.
我非浸淫於其中


291
00:21:46.700 --> 00:21:48.159
That's higher than usual.
簡直是無與能比的興奮


292
00:21:48.244 --> 00:21:50.701
Now, that's what I wanted
Tony to hear you say.
我就是要東尼聽你親口說


293
00:21:50.789 --> 00:21:55.250
I tried to tell him how you feel, but I knew
that you could say it so beautifully.
我試著告訴他你的感覺但是我知道你能說得非常精采


294
00:21:55.336 --> 00:21:57.743
Lily, you splendid animal.
莉莉，你這個造物者的佳作


295
00:21:57.921 --> 00:22:00.837
Take your hands off my wife
and let's get down to business.
別碰我太太，我們談正事吧


296
00:22:00.922 --> 00:22:04.042
Now I have here a script.
It's great. It's ready to roll.
我這裏有一個很棒的劇本已經完成了


297
00:22:04.134 --> 00:22:07.717
Jeff, I want you to take this home.
I want you to read it tonight...
傑夫，我要你今晚帶回家讀


298
00:22:07.804 --> 00:22:10.970
But before I do,
give me a rough idea of the plot.
先把大概的情節告訴我


299
00:22:11.182 --> 00:22:13.720
- Now?
- Throw it at me for a quick impression.
現在?
大致先給我一個印象


300
00:22:13.810 --> 00:22:15.803
- I'm dying to hear it.
- You tell it, Lester.
我迫不急待想聽
李斯特，你說


301
00:22:15.895 --> 00:22:18.136
- You do it so much better.
- Lester, honestly.
你說得精采多了
李斯特，拜託


302
00:22:18.230 --> 00:22:20.721
- Please, Lily, tell them.
- Lester, honestly.
莉莉，拜託，告訴他們
李斯特，拜託


303
00:22:21.567 --> 00:22:25.646
With Tony in mind, we naturally
visualize a light and intimate show.
因為是為東尼寫的
我們想像這是一齣輕快的愛情戲


304
00:22:25.737 --> 00:22:29.736
We want to give him a chance to play
a charming guy, with just enough plot...
我們鋪陳的情節要他飾演一個
魅力十足的帥哥…


305
00:22:29.826 --> 00:22:32.743
to make him do lots
of gay and varied numbers.
剛好能讓他表現很多首愉快的舞曲


306
00:22:33.162 --> 00:22:36.577
He's a writer and illustrator
of children's books...
他是個童書作家兼插畫家


307
00:22:36.665 --> 00:22:38.242
but to get in the real dough...
但是為了賺錢


308
00:22:38.333 --> 00:22:41.417
on the side,
he writes lurid murder mysteries...
他也兼寫駭人聽聞的謀殺懸疑小說


309
00:22:41.502 --> 00:22:43.828
full of violence and buckets of blood.
充滿暴力和血腥


310
00:22:44.590 --> 00:22:47.341
The success of these
makes him feel he's sort of...
他的小說很賣座但是他覺得…


311
00:22:47.425 --> 00:22:50.130
sold his soul to the Devil,
but he keeps on doing it.
把靈魂賣給魔鬼，
好讓他一直做下去。


312
00:22:50.220 --> 00:22:53.552
There's lots of comedy implications
with his friends, played by us.
他和朋友之間蘊藏很多喜劇
我們飾演他的朋友


313
00:22:53.639 --> 00:22:56.391
- And with his girl.
-I love this. Terrific possibilities.
和他的女朋友
我愛死了，很可能賣座


314
00:22:56.475 --> 00:22:58.682
And some of the best numbers
we've ever written!
有一些舞曲是我們寫過最好的


315
00:22:58.769 --> 00:23:03.063
Children's playground, a reform school,

316
00:23:03.148 --> 00:23:06.399
- And a number about a murder mystery!
- You two are the end.
還有一首舞曲是有關謀殺的
你們兩個太棒了


317
00:23:06.652 --> 00:23:10.233
- Tony, I'm so glad!
- Some of the best lines we've written.
東尼，我好高興!
有些是我們寫過最好的對白


318
00:23:11.614 --> 00:23:13.606
What do you think, Jeff?
傑夫，你的看法如何?


319
00:23:21.709 --> 00:23:23.617
Kids, you're geniuses.
年輕人，你們是天才


320
00:23:23.752 --> 00:23:26.668
The whole thing
is a brilliantly imaginative idea.
整個想法真是充滿想像力


321
00:23:26.754 --> 00:23:28.165
Why, Jeff!
為什麼，傑夫！


322
00:23:28.255 --> 00:23:31.873
You've hit on something
that's not only great as a musical...
你們想出來的不只是偉大的音樂劇


323
00:23:31.967 --> 00:23:34.803
but valid in terms of today, of modern life.
而且符合當今社會


324
00:23:34.887 --> 00:23:36.714
Jeff, I'm so glad!
傑夫，我真高興!


325
00:23:36.806 --> 00:23:40.471
Of course, these modern thrillers,
he's got to keep turning them out.
當然，他要繼續寫這些當代驚恐小說


326
00:23:40.559 --> 00:23:42.550
They make him fame, money. He's caught.
這些小說給他名利，他被困住了


327
00:23:42.643 --> 00:23:44.267
It's a funny situation.
是個好笑的情況


328
00:23:44.353 --> 00:23:48.018
Of course! It's brilliant,
contemporary, perceptive.
當然!很精采、很現代化、很有感覺


329
00:23:48.274 --> 00:23:51.394
<i>This story's a modern version of Faust.</i>
這是《浮士德》的現代版


330
00:23:52.986 --> 00:23:55.193
<i>- Faust?
- You're kidding, Jeff.</i>
《浮士德》?
傑夫，你開玩笑吧


331
00:23:56.281 --> 00:23:59.815
I guess I didn't tell it right.
I didn't bring out the point.
我想我說得不好我沒說出重點


332
00:23:59.909 --> 00:24:04.204
But you did bring out the point admirably.
You used the phrase:
但是你的確把重點說得很精采
你用這句話…


333
00:24:04.290 --> 00:24:06.662
"He sells his soul to the Devil."
「他出賣靈魂給魔鬼」


334
00:24:07.042 --> 00:24:10.209
Now, that's the line you have to follow
straight through.
這句話要從頭貫穿到尾


335
00:24:10.462 --> 00:24:13.133
Just like Faust,
this man is tempted by the Devil...
就像浮士德這個人受魔鬼誘惑


336
00:24:13.216 --> 00:24:17.626
and his compromise, his sell-out,
must end in eternal damnation.
他妥協、他背叛自己
要在永恆的毀滅中結束


337
00:24:18.302 --> 00:24:20.211
That'll leave them laughing.
那樣會讓觀眾大笑


338
00:24:20.304 --> 00:24:24.348
Kids, you've got a choice here
between a nice little musical comedy...
你們要一齣不錯的小型音樂喜劇


339
00:24:24.432 --> 00:24:27.269
and a modern musical morality play...
還是要一齣現代化的道德劇


340
00:24:27.353 --> 00:24:29.724
with meaning and stature!
充滿意義和境界


341
00:24:30.439 --> 00:24:34.187
<i>- But we don't want to write Faust.
- You're taking me too literally.</i>
但是我們不想寫《浮士德》
你們把我想得太嚴肅了


342
00:24:34.275 --> 00:24:36.647
I want to do your story. I love it!
我要你們的故事，我愛死了!


343
00:24:36.985 --> 00:24:39.656
But I want to angle it
to bring out the analogy...
但是我要加入一個觀點，帶出


344
00:24:39.739 --> 00:24:42.444
<i>between the Faust legend
and this man's story.</i>
《浮士德》傳奇和這位帥哥之間的類比


345
00:24:43.035 --> 00:24:46.734
Won't this make it heavy?
Is this a box-office idea?
這樣整齣戲不會變得很沉重嗎?
這是票房考慮嗎?


346
00:24:46.829 --> 00:24:48.240
<i>Is Faust box-office?</i>
《浮士德》有票房嗎?


347
00:24:48.331 --> 00:24:51.865
<i>Listen, Faust by Christopher Marlowe,
Faust by Goethe, Faust by Gounod...</i>
聽著，克裏斯多佛馬羅果斯、古諾、赫克特波裏茲


348
00:24:51.959 --> 00:24:53.038
<i>Faust by Hector Berlioz.</i>
都拍過《浮士德》


349
00:24:53.127 --> 00:24:57.125
I tell you, anyone who's touched this
legend has turned it into a gold mine.
我告訴你，碰觸這個傳奇人物就會賺大錢


350
00:24:57.214 --> 00:24:58.838
It's got to be a smash.
定會成功的


351
00:24:59.925 --> 00:25:02.760
It could still have all the fun in it,
couldn't it?
還是可以很有趣，對不對?


352
00:25:02.844 --> 00:25:06.711
- Yeah, and some stature thrown in.
- Now, kids, I'm happy about this.
對，加入一些意境
我很高興


353
00:25:07.015 --> 00:25:09.553
- Really happy.
- So are we, Jeff.
真的
傑夫，我們也是


354
00:25:09.642 --> 00:25:11.101
This publisher you mentioned...
你說的那個出版商


355
00:25:11.186 --> 00:25:14.055
obviously, he could be
the counterpart of the Devil.
很顯然他就是魔鬼


356
00:25:18.860 --> 00:25:20.899
Evil personified!
擬人化的魔鬼


357
00:25:21.529 --> 00:25:25.655
Leading all mankind
into the paths of temptation!
把所有的人類帶上誘惑之路!


358
00:25:26.407 --> 00:25:29.907
- But nobody could play it like you.
- Nobody's going to.
但是沒有人能演得跟你一樣
不用找其他人演


359
00:25:29.994 --> 00:25:32.071
You mean you're going to play it?
你的意思是你要演？


360
00:25:32.414 --> 00:25:35.331
The part of the girl... Somebody fresh.
那個女主角—定要找新面孔


361
00:25:35.417 --> 00:25:39.200
Somebody with fire, charm, grace, beauty.
Gabrielle Gerard.
一個有熱情、迷人、優雅、美麗
蓋布莉亞傑若傑若?


362
00:25:39.378 --> 00:25:42.748
- Gerard? She's a ballet dancer.
- She doesn't want to do a show.
傑若?她是芭蕾舞者
她不想參加舞台劇演出


363
00:25:42.840 --> 00:25:45.332
- She turns them all down.
- Nobody ever turns me down.
她婉拒所有的邀約
沒有人能拒絕我


364
00:25:45.427 --> 00:25:48.262
Do you really think you could get her?
What a cast!
你真的認為能找她來演?
多麼堅強的陣容!


365
00:25:48.346 --> 00:25:52.972
Tony Hunter, Jeff Cordova,
Gabrielle Gerard! Tony! Isn't this exciting?
東尼杭特、傑夫可多瓦、
蓋布莉亞傑若，是不是很棒?


366
00:25:53.059 --> 00:25:54.257
Yeah.
對


367
00:25:54.685 --> 00:25:58.432
<i>Now, look, this is going to be
a sort of modern Faust story.</i>
聽著，這有點像現代版的《浮士德》


368
00:25:59.105 --> 00:26:03.351
I play the Faust character. You play
the Devil. It'll have stature, importance.
我演浮士德，你演魔鬼都有寓意，很重要


369
00:26:03.775 --> 00:26:06.693
- I have to dance with this ballet dancer?
- She's wonderful.
我要和芭蕾舞者共舞?
她很棒


370
00:26:06.779 --> 00:26:07.978
It'll be great.
好極了


371
00:26:08.073 --> 00:26:11.441
It'll be great for somebody.
I'll pick up my marbles and go home.
對某人來說很棒
我要收拾東西回家了


372
00:26:11.534 --> 00:26:14.450
Fellas, bless you and good luck,
but this just ain't for me.
大夥兒，祝一切順利
但這不是我的戲


373
00:26:14.536 --> 00:26:16.529
I know what I can do,
and I'm sticking to it.
我知道我的長處，
而且不想改變


374
00:26:16.622 --> 00:26:19.742
That's the trouble. You've stuck to it,
and you're stuck with it.
問題就出在這裏，
你不想改變你就改變不了


375
00:26:19.833 --> 00:26:22.372
- What?
- Tony, nobody admires you more than I.
什麼?
東尼，沒有人比我更仰慕你


376
00:26:22.462 --> 00:26:25.581
I've seen every show
and every movie you've ever done...
你演過的每齣舞台劇
拍過的每部電影我都看過


377
00:26:25.673 --> 00:26:27.381
but let's face some brutal facts.
但是讓我們面對殘酷的現實


378
00:26:27.466 --> 00:26:30.584
Times have changed, Tony.
You haven't changed with them.
東尼，時代改變了
你沒跟著一起變


379
00:26:30.676 --> 00:26:34.721
- You've gone stale.
- Then you certainly don't need me.
你過氣了
那你就不需要我了


380
00:26:35.682 --> 00:26:37.140
Yes, we do!
我們需要!


381
00:26:37.225 --> 00:26:39.632
Because you can be greater
than you ever were!
因為你可以比以前更好!


382
00:26:39.727 --> 00:26:43.345
We are going to make you explode
on the theatre scene like a skyrocket!
我們要讓你像火箭一樣引爆劇場!


383
00:26:43.439 --> 00:26:46.475
Not just the old trademark,
with the top hat, tie, and tails...
不只是戴禮帽、穿燕尾服的老商標!


384
00:26:46.566 --> 00:26:48.642
but a great artist
at the peak of his powers.
而是正值巔峰時期的偉大藝術家


385
00:26:48.735 --> 00:26:52.484
The new Tony Hunter. Tony Hunter, 1953!
新的東尼杭特，l953年東山再起!


386
00:26:52.573 --> 00:26:55.692
- But can I do it?
- It's a challenge to all of us...
但是我辦得到嗎?
對我們大家都是挑戰


387
00:26:55.783 --> 00:26:58.357
but that's what the theatre�s about:
a challenge.
劇場就是：挑戰


388
00:26:58.453 --> 00:27:00.826
Whatever I am,
whether it's a new me or an old me...
不管我是什麼，
是新的我還是過去的我…


389
00:27:00.915 --> 00:27:02.705
remember, I'm still just an entertainer.
記住，我還是個藝人


390
00:27:02.791 --> 00:27:05.281
What do you think I am?
What do you think they are?
你以為我是什麼?
你以為他們是什麼?


391
00:27:05.376 --> 00:27:08.045
What do you think the theatre is?
It's all entertainment!
你以為劇場是什麼?
全就是為娛樂!


392
00:27:08.129 --> 00:27:11.248
Believe me, there is no difference
between the magic rhythms...
相信我，沒有區別
神奇的節奏與...


393
00:27:11.340 --> 00:27:14.046
- of Bill Robinson's immortal feet...
- You said that before.
比爾羅賓遜的不朽腳..
你說過了


394
00:27:14.135 --> 00:27:17.835
All right, what did Bill Robinson do?
He danced on the stairs, didn't he?
好，比爾羅賓森做了什麼?
他在階梯上跳舞，不是嗎?


395
00:27:17.930 --> 00:27:20.599
Now I happen to play Oedipus the king
on the same stairs.
現在我剛好站在相同的階梯
上演伊底帕斯王


396
00:27:20.682 --> 00:27:23.172
What's the difference? We're all theatre.
有什麼差別?我們都在相同的劇中


397
00:27:24.268 --> 00:27:25.894
Show me the greatest tragic actor...
給我最棒的悲劇演員


398
00:27:25.979 --> 00:27:28.186
or the lowest red-nosed comic
in burlesque...
或粗俗歌舞劇裏的丑角


399
00:27:28.273 --> 00:27:30.811
and I'll show you an entertainer. We're all...
我就表演給你藝人，我們都是你藝人


400
00:27:32.694 --> 00:27:34.687
Jeff, are you all right?
傑夫，你還好吧?


401
00:27:35.363 --> 00:27:37.853
<i>Everything that happens in life</i>
人生的每個遭遇


402
00:27:38.031 --> 00:27:40.403
<i>can happen in a show</i>
戲劇都能呈現


403
00:27:40.992 --> 00:27:44.196
<i>You can make 'em laugh
You can make 'em cry</i>
你能讓他們大笑你能讓他們哭泣


404
00:27:44.620 --> 00:27:48.666
<i>Anything, anything can go</i>
任何事，任何事都能呈現


405
00:27:51.338 --> 00:27:54.586
<i>The clown with his pants falling down</i>
小丑的褲子掉下來


406
00:27:54.673 --> 00:27:58.172
<i>Or the dance that's a dream of romance</i>
或是舞出浪漫夢想


407
00:27:58.260 --> 00:28:02.304
<i>Or the scene where the villain is mean</i>
或是出現兇狠壞蛋


408
00:28:03.056 --> 00:28:05.630
<i>That's Entertainment!</i>
那就是娛樂!


409
00:28:06.102 --> 00:28:09.221
<i>The lights on the lady in tights</i>
燈光打在穿緊身衣的女士身土


410
00:28:09.312 --> 00:28:13.059
<i>Or the bride with the guy on the side</i>
或是新郎站在新娘身旁


411
00:28:13.148 --> 00:28:17.312
<i>Or the ball where she gives him her all</i>
或是她舞出對他全部的愛


412
00:28:17.778 --> 00:28:20.351
<i>That's Entertainment!</i>
那就是娛樂!


413
00:28:20.947 --> 00:28:24.150
<i>The plot can be hot
