<i>the stage is a world of entertainment</i>
這個舞台是娛樂的世界


444
00:31:03.182 --> 00:31:06.303
- You gone yet, Hal?
- I'm in here, Jeff, on the phone.
哈爾，你走了嗎?
傑夫，我在這裏，在打電話


445
00:31:06.437 --> 00:31:09.009
Drama desk? Hello, Mike. It's Hal.
影劇組?嗨，麥克，我是哈爾


446
00:31:09.147 --> 00:31:12.682
You know that item Mr. Cordova sent you
about signing Gabrielle Gerard...
你知道可多瓦先生寄給你的劇本
說蓋布莉亞傑若要演出…


447
00:31:12.776 --> 00:31:13.939
for the Marton show?
莫頓的戲?


448
00:31:14.027 --> 00:31:17.609
There's been a mistake.
I wonder if there's still time to kill it.
那是個錯誤，不知道能不能取消


449
00:31:17.697 --> 00:31:20.615
- Yeah. I'd appreciate it. Thanks, kid.
- Why did you do that?
好，謝謝
你為什麼要這樣做?


450
00:31:20.700 --> 00:31:23.273
To save you from making an idiot
of yourself in print.
讓你不會被媒體取笑


451
00:31:23.369 --> 00:31:25.776
- You know you can't get Gerard.
- Why?
你知道不可能弄到傑若
為什麼?


452
00:31:25.871 --> 00:31:29.371
Because Paul Byrd won't let her
do a show. He's a tough customer.
因為保羅拜德不會讓她參與舞台劇演出，
他很難搞


453
00:31:29.458 --> 00:31:32.209
He's not only her choreographer,
he's also her boyfriend.
他不只是她的編舞，
也是她的男友


454
00:31:32.294 --> 00:31:34.085
She doesn't make a move without him.
他說不行她就不接


455
00:31:34.171 --> 00:31:36.128
That will be Paul Byrd now.
那一定是保羅拜德


456
00:31:36.215 --> 00:31:39.583
- It's 3:00 in the morning.
- Let him in, Hal, will you?
現在是淩晨3點
哈爾，讓他進來，好嗎?


457
00:31:44.306 --> 00:31:45.800
- Hello, Paul.
- Where are they?
嗨，保羅
他們在哪裏?


458
00:31:45.891 --> 00:31:47.385
He's in there.
他在裏面


459
00:31:47.768 --> 00:31:48.929
Hello, Paul.
嗨，保羅


460
00:31:49.018 --> 00:31:50.393
- Where is he?
- Who?
他在哪裏？
誰？


461
00:31:50.478 --> 00:31:53.050
- Oscar Hammerstein.
- Home in bed, I hope, at this hour.
奧斯卡漠莫斯坦
這個時間，我想他上床了


462
00:31:53.146 --> 00:31:55.769
- Who is it? Dick Rodgers?
- What are you talking about?
那是誰?狄克羅傑斯?
你在說什麼?


463
00:31:55.859 --> 00:31:58.528
Didn't you say the greatest producer
of musicals today...
你不是說當今最好的音樂劇製作人


464
00:31:58.611 --> 00:31:59.939
was here and wanted to see me?
想見我嗎?


465
00:32:00.029 --> 00:32:03.896
- That's me. I'm doing a musical.
- Did you get me out of bed...
那是我，我要導一齣音樂劇
你把我從床上叫起來…


466
00:32:07.701 --> 00:32:09.244
I see what this is all about.
我知道你要什麼了


467
00:32:09.328 --> 00:32:13.195
You needn't go any further because
the answer is no on Gabrielle Gerard.
你不用多說什麼
因為要找蓋布莉亞，答案是不


468
00:32:13.290 --> 00:32:15.698
Gabrielle... Paul, I don't follow you.
蓋布莉亞…保羅，我不懂


469
00:32:15.793 --> 00:32:18.997
Gabrielle is not going to do a show.
She's too important to ballet.
蓋布莉亞不會參加舞台劇演出
她對芭蕾舞界太重要了


470
00:32:19.089 --> 00:32:20.796
This has nothing to do with Gabrielle.
這和蓋布莉亞毫無關係


471
00:32:21.341 --> 00:32:25.504
Paul, I want you to do the choreography
for the greatest musical in years.
保羅，我要你為這齣
幾年來最好的音樂劇編舞


472
00:32:28.013 --> 00:32:30.136
- I'm sorry...
- That's why I wakened you, Paul.
對不起…保羅，
這就是我要的


473
00:32:30.224 --> 00:32:34.092
I'm so keyed up I just can't sleep.
You know how brilliant the Martons are.
我興奮到睡不著你知道
莫頓夫婦有多棒


474
00:32:34.187 --> 00:32:35.930
This time, they've excelled themselves.
這一次，他們再度超越自己


475
00:32:36.022 --> 00:32:38.937
This show is a choreographer's dream,
and only you can do it.
這齣戲是編舞夢寐以求的只有你辦得到


476
00:32:39.023 --> 00:32:41.728
- I wouldn't say that.
- No time for false modesty.
我不敢講
沒時間假惺惺了


477
00:32:41.817 --> 00:32:44.818
You're the greatest, and we know it.
This is just your meat.
你是最棒的，而且我們都知道
這是你的專長


478
00:32:44.903 --> 00:32:49.530
<i>A great classic theme.
The story of Faust in a modern setting.</i>
你是最棒的，而且我們都知道
這是你的專長


479
00:32:51.410 --> 00:32:54.281
Say, that sounds interesting.
聽起來很有趣


480
00:32:54.371 --> 00:32:57.240
I've never been so excited
about a project in my life.
我一生中還不曾為一齣戲這麼興奮過


481
00:32:57.331 --> 00:33:01.033
Now, there's Tony Hunter, myself,
a great score by the Martons.
有東尼杭特、我自己音樂是莫頓夫婦寫的


482
00:33:01.128 --> 00:33:03.501
Wonderful. My brain's beginning
to churn already.
太棒了，我的腦筋開始動個不停


483
00:33:03.590 --> 00:33:07.373
Good. Now we must comb the country
for a wonderful singer for the girl.
好，我們現在要找一個很棒的歌手
來演這個女士角


484
00:33:07.676 --> 00:33:11.341
Singer? Jeff, don't you think we ought
to stress the dancing in that role?
歌手?傑夫，你不覺得我們該強調這個角色的舞技?


485
00:33:11.429 --> 00:33:12.673
No, Paul.
不，保羅


486
00:33:12.763 --> 00:33:17.390
This girl has to be a virtuoso performer,
with fire, charm, beauty...
這個女士角一定要有大師級
演得出熱情、迷人、美麗…


487
00:33:17.518 --> 00:33:21.598
a great lady with a gamine quality.
You know no dancer can give you that.
還帶點調皮你知道
沒有舞者具備這樣的特質


488
00:33:21.688 --> 00:33:25.733
Wait. Of course I wouldn't let her do it,
but Gabrielle has all that and more.
等等，當然我不會讓蓋布莉亞參與
但這些特質她都有


489
00:33:25.818 --> 00:33:29.068
Gabrielle? Paul, I feel a little embarrassed.
蓋布莉亞? 保羅，我覺得不太好意思


490
00:33:29.155 --> 00:33:32.071
I think she's charming,
within her limitations. Charming.
她很迷人，但並非全能，迷人而已


491
00:33:32.157 --> 00:33:33.899
She's a great artist, and you know it.
她很棒，你很清楚


492
00:33:33.991 --> 00:33:37.491
- Sorry. I know how fond of her you are.
- That has nothing to do with it!
對不起，我知道你非常喜歡她
這跟那個無關!


493
00:33:37.578 --> 00:33:39.952
She can be one of the greatest
stars in the theatre.
她可以成為劇場最閃亮的明星


494
00:33:40.040 --> 00:33:41.534
Everybody's been trying to get her.
大家都想要她


495
00:33:41.624 --> 00:33:43.866
For the right vehicle,
something light and fluffy.
只要劇本對了輕鬆又沒有很多對白


496
00:33:43.960 --> 00:33:45.620
Light and fluffy? Now, see here, Jeff.
輕鬆又沒有很多對白?傑夫


497
00:33:45.712 --> 00:33:49.162
I'm not gonna do this show
unless Gabrielle Gerard plays that part!
除非蓋布莉亞傑若參與這齣戲
否則我不願插手!


498
00:33:49.381 --> 00:33:53.082
Now, Paul, this throws a little
monkey wrench into things, doesn't it?
保羅，這樣很難再談下去，不是嗎?


499
00:33:53.177 --> 00:33:56.131
Never mind.
You and I will work together sometime...
無所謂，我們會有機會合作


500
00:33:56.221 --> 00:33:59.472
Wait. At least do this. You come
and see her in the ballet tomorrow.
等等，這樣好了你明天來看她跳芭蕾舞


501
00:33:59.558 --> 00:34:02.048
- Bring Hunter, bring the Martons.
- No. Impossible.
把杭特和莫頓夫婦一起帶來
不，不可能


502
00:34:02.143 --> 00:34:04.765
I have a performance.
But I'll gladly send the Martons.
我有演出，但我很樂意派莫頓夫婦過去


503
00:34:04.854 --> 00:34:08.389
We can get together afterwards and talk.
Mind you, I'm promising nothing.
散場後我們可以聚在一起聊聊
提醒你，我不敢保證


504
00:34:08.483 --> 00:34:10.274
Good night, sweetie.
親愛的，晚安


505
00:34:12.653 --> 00:34:13.934
Drama desk?
影劇組?


506
00:34:14.030 --> 00:34:17.648
Mike. Hal again.
Better print that item after all.
麥克，又是我
哈爾還是讓那篇報導上報吧


507
00:34:17.742 --> 00:34:22.153
And, Mike, after this, if Mr. Cordova tells
you he's casting Tallulah...
還有麥克，如果可多瓦先生
告訴你他要請塔盧拉…


508
00:34:22.328 --> 00:34:24.866
for Little Eva, believe him.
演出《小伊娃》，相信他


509
00:34:29.418 --> 00:34:30.796
COMMODORE THEATER
Coutray Ballet Company
康莫朵劇場庫崔芭蕾舞團


510
00:34:30.880 --> 00:34:33.086
Gabrielle Gerard
Choreography by Paul Byrd
蓋布莉亞傑若編舞保羅拜德


511
00:34:33.173 --> 00:34:36.128
IMAGE OF THE NIGHT - ENSEMBLE
THE FIELDS - PHANTASY
夜晚的印象—田野合唱
幻想曲


512
00:35:44.238 --> 00:35:45.318
Well?
怎麼樣?


513
00:35:45.406 --> 00:35:48.527
She's fabulous, sensational,
loveliest thing I've ever seen.
她很棒，是我見過最有感情最可愛的人


514
00:36:25.236 --> 00:36:26.981
A little tall, isn't she?
有點高，是不是?


515
00:36:28.073 --> 00:36:29.615
Stage illusion.
舞台效果


516
00:37:06.318 --> 00:37:08.060
So you didn't care for it much?
你不是很在意?


517
00:37:08.151 --> 00:37:10.061
The girl's fantastic, beautiful...
她太棒了，又美麗


518
00:37:10.153 --> 00:37:11.647
but I can't dance with her.
可是我無法和她共舞


519
00:37:11.737 --> 00:37:13.232
Stop worrying!
別擔心!


520
00:37:16.785 --> 00:37:19.572
It isn't that I don't appreciate
what she does.
並不是我不欣賞她


521
00:37:19.663 --> 00:37:22.580
I tell you, I know she's magnificent.
That's what scares me.
我告訴你，我知道她很傑出
所以我才擔心


522
00:37:22.666 --> 00:37:26.329
But I haven't done ballet
since I was a kid. I'd look silly.
我只有小時候跳過芭蕾
我跳起來很蠢


523
00:37:26.668 --> 00:37:28.460
Hello, Lil. You look wonderful.
Put your things over there.
嗨，莉莉，你真漂亮
把東西放在這裏


524
00:37:29.546 --> 00:37:30.924
Hello, Mr. Hunter. How are you?
杭特先生，你好?


525
00:37:31.008 --> 00:37:32.964
- Hello, Les. Glad to see you.
- How are you?
嗨，李斯，見到你真好
你好


526
00:37:33.051 --> 00:37:35.376
What is this?
The annual fur trappers' convention?
這是什麼?
年度捕貂大會?


527
00:37:35.470 --> 00:37:37.712
- The boss is inside with big money.
- His backers?
老闆和有錢人在裏面
他的贊助者?


528
00:37:37.806 --> 00:37:40.261
- They're raising money for the show.
- What show, ours?
他們為這齣戲募款
哪齣戲，我們的?


529
00:37:40.349 --> 00:37:42.257
- Sure.
- He hasn't read the script yet.
對
他還沒讀過劇本


530
00:37:42.349 --> 00:37:44.094
- I better go back...
- Sorry, Mr. Marton.
我還是回去...
抱歉!莫頓先生


531
00:37:44.186 --> 00:37:47.352
You disturb the water, you scare the fish.
They're biting tonight.
別嚇跑這些肥魚，
他們今晚要上鉤了


532
00:37:47.438 --> 00:37:50.392
- What's he telling them?
- Whatever it is, it's going over big.
他跟他們說什麼?
不管說什麼，他們都會非常興奮


533
00:37:50.483 --> 00:37:52.143
- Come on, Lil.
- Please don't go in yet.
來，莉莉
拜託還不要進去


534
00:37:52.235 --> 00:37:55.069
Wait here in the study.
He's saving you for the big finale.
在工作室等，
他會讓你們在終場時亮相


535
00:37:55.154 --> 00:37:56.186
Excuse me.
失陪一下


536
00:37:56.281 --> 00:37:58.273
- Lester, isn't this wonderful?
- Yeah.
李斯特，這不是很好嗎?
對


537
00:37:58.366 --> 00:38:00.654
- This is going to be great, Tony.
- Why?
東尼，一切都會很棒
為什麼?


538
00:38:00.743 --> 00:38:02.984
Cordova. The dough for the show.
No problems.
可多瓦是這齣戲的賣點，
沒問題


539
00:38:03.078 --> 00:38:05.486
How many times did we have to audition
the last time?
我們最後一齣戲辦了多少場試聽


540
00:38:05.581 --> 00:38:07.538
- Fifty.
- A hundred, maybe more.

541
00:38:07.624 --> 00:38:11.623
Jeff might raise the backing tonight.
We'll be ready to rehearse in three weeks.
今晚傑夫可能籌到經費
我們3星期內就能進行排演


542
00:38:13.089 --> 00:38:14.879
- Hello, Hal.
- Hello, Paul. How are you?
嗨 哈爾
嗨 保羅


543
00:38:14.965 --> 00:38:16.624
How nice to see you. Come right in.
見到你真好，請進


544
00:38:16.716 --> 00:38:18.755
Hal, this is Miss Gerard. Mr. Benton.
哈爾，傑若小姐，班頓先生


545
00:38:18.843 --> 00:38:21.049
How do you do?
Jeff's inside with the backers.
你好，
傑夫和出資者在裏面


546
00:38:21.137 --> 00:38:23.047
Why don't you wait in the library?
你們何不在書房等?


547
00:38:23.140 --> 00:38:24.598
- Excuse me.
- Thanks.
失陪
謝謝


548
00:38:31.021 --> 00:38:33.227
Let's wait in here a minute, huh?
讓我們等待在這裡一分鐘，對吧？


549
00:38:34.400 --> 00:38:36.725
Now, wait a second. I'm not ready yet.
等一下，找還沒準備好


550
00:38:36.819 --> 00:38:38.692
There's a lot to be cleared up first.
有很多事要先釐清


551
00:38:38.779 --> 00:38:41.235
This girl Gerard, it's not just her dancing.
這個叫傑若的女演員不只是她的舞蹈


552
00:38:41.323 --> 00:38:44.692
On top of everything, she's too tall for me.
This girl is a giantess.
她對我來說太高了，她是個女巨人


553
00:38:44.785 --> 00:38:46.860
She's not too tall for you. I know this girl.
她不會太高，我認識她


554
00:38:46.953 --> 00:38:49.159
She comes up to here,
maybe 2 inches shorter.
她大概到我這裏，也許再矮個5公分


555
00:38:49.246 --> 00:38:51.619
You know I'm the perfect height for you.
Now look...
你知道我跟你身高很配，聽著


556
00:38:51.707 --> 00:38:54.114
turn around. Measure. Look.
You see? Isn't that fine?
轉過去，比比看你看?
不是剛剛好?


557
00:38:54.209 --> 00:38:59.037
Listen. Gabrielle Gerard in her
stocking feet is at the most 3-feet tall.
聽著，蓋布莉亞傑若就算光腳
也只有9O公分


558
00:38:59.505 --> 00:39:03.422
Now relax. I'm going to find you a drink,
and you can stop worrying about her.
放輕鬆，我幫你倒杯飲料
你不要再擔心她的事


559
00:39:03.512 --> 00:39:06.215
Jeff only wants her in the show
because she's the best.
傑夫指定要她，
因為她是最棒的


560
00:39:06.305 --> 00:39:08.760
We all gotta go along with him, too, Tony.
東尼，我們都要聽他的


561
00:39:08.849 --> 00:39:11.007
In the show, one guy's got to be
at the helm...
戲劇只能由一個人來主導·


562
00:39:11.101 --> 00:39:13.640
and in Jeff, we got someone
we can trust to...
傑夫是我們能信任的人


563
00:39:13.730 --> 00:39:17.347
...it is the Devil, come to claim the soul
of the modern Faust man.
魔鬼要來奪走現代浮士德的靈魂


564
00:39:17.441 --> 00:39:20.359
With flapping wings
and grinning evil eyes...
他鼓動雙翅，邪惡的雙眼冷冷地笑


565
00:39:20.444 --> 00:39:23.229
he points the way
to the yawning pits of Hades.
他指向冥王打哈欠的大嘴


566
00:39:26.824 --> 00:39:27.939
Hallelujah.
好極了


567
00:39:29.159 --> 00:39:31.401
- I'm embarrassed.
- Don't be childish.
我不好意思了
別孩子氣了


568
00:39:31.495 --> 00:39:34.033
I'm sure Tony Hunter doesn't want me
in this show.
我知道東尼杭特
不希望我參與這齣戲


569
00:39:34.123 --> 00:39:36.992
- What makes you say that?
- Did he come backstage to see me...
你為什麼會這樣說?
散場後他有沒有…


570
00:39:37.083 --> 00:39:38.246
after the performance?
到後台看我?


571
00:39:38.334 --> 00:39:40.244
He knew he was going to meet you here.
他知道他會在這裏見到你


572
00:39:40.337 --> 00:39:44.168
- I'm just a ballet dancer...
- You're a famous leading ballerina.
我只是個芭蕾舞者…
你是當紅的首席芭蕾舞者


573
00:39:44.256 --> 00:39:47.591
What does he want with me?
He's a famous movie and stage actor.
他為什麼找我?
他是知名的電影明星和舞台劇演員


574
00:39:47.678 --> 00:39:50.429
He's practically a historical character
by now.
他現在簡直就是傳奇人物


575
00:39:50.513 --> 00:39:53.930
Dancing with him is like dancing
with a statue of General Grant.
跟他跳舞
就像跟格蘭特將軍的雕像跳舞一樣


576
00:39:54.018 --> 00:39:55.558
Now look, Gaby.
蓋比，聽著


577
00:39:55.976 --> 00:39:59.558
You know, this is a Cordova show.
It's an important step for you.
你知道這是可多瓦的戲
對你是很重要的一步


578
00:39:59.646 --> 00:40:03.726
I'm going to do the choreography,
so there's nothing for you to worry about.
編舞由我負責，所以你不用擔心


579
00:40:03.817 --> 00:40:06.688
But I still think he doesn't want me
in the show.
但是找還是覺得他不會要我


580
00:40:06.862 --> 00:40:08.273
Your nose is shiny.
你鼻子出油了


581
00:40:08.363 --> 00:40:10.605
- Where's the...
- Maybe this is it.
你鼻子出油了


582
00:40:12.200 --> 00:40:16.992
He passes by all the writhing souls
in torment paying for their deadly sins.
他與所有掙紮的靈魂擦身而過
見他們用痛苦償還深重的罪孽


583
00:40:17.079 --> 00:40:18.907
Gluttony, avarice...
暴食、貪婪


584
00:40:20.875 --> 00:40:22.369
It must be upstairs.
一定在樓上


585
00:40:40.143 --> 00:40:42.016
Lester, what have we got ourselves into?
李斯特，事情怎麼會這樣?


586
00:40:42.103 --> 00:40:45.555
The story he's telling them has nothing
to do with the story we wrote.
他說的故事跟我們寫的毫無關係


587
00:40:45.649 --> 00:40:48.104
This will mean months of rewriting.
這表示要再花幾個月重寫


588
00:40:48.317 --> 00:40:51.520
He expects us to go into rehearsal
in three weeks?
他要我們三個星期內就進行排演?


589
00:40:55.782 --> 00:41:00.611
Brimstone and flames. Save me.
地獄的火焰，拯救我


590
00:41:07.710 --> 00:41:12.538
Corrupter of children.
Purveyor of evil. Dungeon...
使兒童墮落的人供養邪惡的人，地獄裏


591
00:41:14.051 --> 00:41:18.463
...bubbling cauldrons.
Fiery furnaces of doom.
滾燙的油鍋，毀滅的炙熱熔爐


592
00:41:26.562 --> 00:41:29.018
- You're...
- And you're... How do you do?
你是…
你是?你好


593
00:41:29.106 --> 00:41:30.898
How do you do? It's certainly a...
你好，這真的是


594
00:41:30.983 --> 00:41:34.019
- We've been waiting for you in there.
- We just got here.
我們一直在裏面等
我們才到


595
00:41:34.111 --> 00:41:36.435
We just got here ourselves,
about five minutes ago.
我們大概五分鐘前到的


596
00:41:36.529 --> 00:41:38.652
A little early, I guess. Mr. Cordova's busy.
我猜來得有點早，可多瓦先生很忙


597
00:41:38.740 --> 00:41:41.277
Yes, I know, and I rushed so to get here.
對，我知道，我匆忙趕過來


598
00:41:41.367 --> 00:41:43.858
- I'm a mess.
- No. You look wonderful.
沒有好好打扮
不，你很漂亮


599
00:41:45.412 --> 00:41:48.497
- Will you have a cigarette?
- No, thanks. I don't smoke.
沒有好好打扮不，你很漂亮


600
00:41:48.624 --> 00:41:51.709
- Never?
- I don't think a dancer should smoke.
從來沒抽過?
我覺得舞者不該抽煙


601
00:41:51.794 --> 00:41:52.957
I see.
我懂了


602
00:41:54.086 --> 00:41:56.957
- Is anything wrong?
- No.
怎麼啦?
沒事


603
00:41:57.715 --> 00:41:59.756
- Pretty shoes.
- Thank you.
鞋子很漂亮
謝謝


604
00:42:00.052 --> 00:42:01.712
You always wear high heels?
你都穿高跟鞋嗎?


605
00:42:01.804 --> 00:42:04.295
No. Not always. Sometimes toeshoes.
不，有時候穿芭蕾鞋


606
00:42:04.724 --> 00:42:06.004
Toeshoes.
芭蕾舞鞋


607
00:42:06.225 --> 00:42:08.134
I'm afraid I've been awfully rude.
我真是失禮


608
00:42:08.227 --> 00:42:10.846
I haven't told you how wonderful
you were tonight.
我還沒告訴你
你今晚的演出有多精采


609
00:42:10.936 --> 00:42:13.724
Thank you.
I'm a great admirer of yours, too.
謝謝，
我也非常欣賞你


610
00:42:13.815 --> 00:42:16.601
- I didn't think you'd ever even heard of me.
- Heard of you?
我以為你沒聽過我的名字
沒聽過你?


611
00:42:16.692 --> 00:42:19.444
I used to see all your pictures
when I was a little girl.
我從小時候就看過你每部電影


612
00:42:19.528 --> 00:42:23.193
I'm still a fan. I recently went to see
a revival of them at the museum.
我還是你的影迷，最近博物館重新播出，
找還去看了


613
00:42:23.281 --> 00:42:24.361
Museum?
博物館?


614
00:42:24.449 --> 00:42:26.324
"Step right this way,
ladies and gentlemen.
各位先生女士，往這邊站


615
00:42:26.411 --> 00:42:28.319
"Egyptian mummies, extinct reptiles...
埃及木乃伊、絕種的爬蟲類


616
00:42:28.412 --> 00:42:31.246
"and Tony Hunter,
the grand old man of the dance."
還有東尼杭特，偉大的舞者。


617
00:42:31.331 --> 00:42:32.410
I didn't mean...
我意思不是....


618
00:42:32.498 --> 00:42:36.449
I want you to know that I can still
thread a needle without my eyeglasses...
我告訴你不用戴眼鏡我一樣能穿針


619
00:42:36.544 --> 00:42:39.380
and still occasionally do
a soft-shoe shuffle.
還有偶爾不穿踢踏舞鞋還能跳踢踏舞


620
00:42:39.464 --> 00:42:41.042
Nothing balletic, of course.
當然，與芭蕾舞無關


621
00:42:41.133 --> 00:42:43.042
You're not a ballet devotee, are you?
你不熱衷芭蕾舞，是不是?


622
00:42:43.135 --> 00:42:45.754
Yes. I was going to the ballet
before you were born.
對，我看芭蕾舞表演時你還沒出生


623
00:42:45.844 --> 00:42:49.011
I saw Pavlova, Karsavina,
all the real ballet greats.
我見過巴甫洛娃、卡莎維娜
以及所有真正的大師


624
00:42:49.098 --> 00:42:51.803
You don't see dancing like that nowadays.
I'm sorry.
現在看不到這樣的舞技了，對不起


625
00:42:51.892 --> 00:42:54.597
That's okay. I don't expect you
to class me with Pavlova.
沒關係，我不期望你把我
跟巴甫洛娃相提並論


626
00:42:54.687 --> 00:42:55.932
In fact, if she were around...
如果她還在


627
00:42:56.022 --> 00:42:58.264
I doubt if she'd be good enough
to dance with you.
她可能還不夠格跟你跳舞


628
00:42:58.357 --> 00:43:00.432
You'd probably insist on an audition first.
你說不定要她先試鏡


629
00:43:00.524 --> 00:43:03.276
I sure would.
I'd audition my own grandmother.
我一定會，就算我祖母我都要她試鏡


630
00:43:03.361 --> 00:43:06.979
Then why don't you audition mine?
She'd be just about right for you.
那你為什麼不找我祖母試鏡?
她跟你說不定最速配


631
00:43:07.073 --> 00:43:09.232
- I'm terribly sorry.
- No, you're not.
真是對不起
不 你說謊


632
00:43:09.325 --> 00:43:10.820
- No, I'm not.
- Neither am I.
對 我沒錯
我也是


633
00:43:10.911 --> 00:43:11.990
Good.
好


634
00:43:16.707 --> 00:43:19.494
- Paul, I'm leaving.
- What's the matter, darling?
保羅，我要走了
親愛的，怎麼啦?


635
00:43:19.584 --> 00:43:21.742
I can't work with that man.
He's impossible.
我無法和這個人共事，
與他這不可能


636
00:43:21.836 --> 00:43:23.544
We just got here. It'll look funny...
我們才剛到，會有點可笑


637
00:43:23.629 --> 00:43:26.334
The whole thing is off.
This girl is a monster.
整件事吹了，那個女人是個魔鬼


638
00:43:26.424 --> 00:43:28.417
I have definitely had it.
我受夠了


639
00:43:29.761 --> 00:43:33.842
And now, ladies and gentlemen,
the brains, the talent, the artists.
各位先生女士，天才編劇、藝人


640
00:43:34.474 --> 00:43:36.881
Wonderful. Aren't they wonderful?
太好了，他們是不是很棒?


641
00:43:43.316 --> 00:43:45.558
You have no idea
how well things are going.
你們不知道事情進行得多順利


642
00:43:45.652 --> 00:43:47.395
It's really wonderful.
真的很棒


643
00:43:48.488 --> 00:43:50.361
Ladies and gentlemen.
各位先生女士


644
00:43:50.448 --> 00:43:52.854
I want you all to meet
the happy little group...
這就是我們快樂的小團隊


645
00:43:52.948 --> 00:43:54.491
that's responsible for the show...
他們負責這齣戲的演出


646
00:43:54.575 --> 00:43:57.826
that everyone will be clamouring
to get seats for next season.
將是下一季的票房保證


647
00:43:57.912 --> 00:44:00.664
The celebrated choreographer Paul Byrd.
著名的編舞保羅拜德


648
00:44:03.209 --> 00:44:07.158
The authors you know:
Lily and Lester Marton.
你們都知道的編劇
莉莉和李斯特莫頓


649
00:44:07.421 --> 00:44:09.081
Take a bow, Lily.
莉莉，謝謝大家


650
00:44:09.715 --> 00:44:11.672
And, ladies and gentlemen...
還有，各位先生女士


651
00:44:11.758 --> 00:44:14.001
my star, Tony Hunter.
我的明星，東尼杭特


652
00:44:14.095 --> 00:44:17.547
A name, a talent.
Mr. Show Business himself.
這個名字是個天才
他自己就是演藝事業


653
00:44:20.267 --> 00:44:23.519
And, ladies and gentlemen,
his new leading lady.
還有，各位先生女土
他的新搭檔女士角


654
00:44:23.605 --> 00:44:27.683
That glamorous, delightful dancer
from the magical world of ballet.
來自奇妙的芭蕾舞世界
一個典雅可愛的舞者


655
00:44:27.773 --> 00:44:31.818
Mr. Hunter's own personal choice,
Gabrielle Gerard.
杭特先生指定的人選，
蓋布莉亞傑若


656
00:44:34.488 --> 00:44:38.154
I think, gentlemen, you will agree
your investment is safe, yes?
我想各位都同意
你們的投資沒有風險，是嗎?


657
00:44:38.243 --> 00:44:41.077
Now let's relax and have a drink, shall we?
讓我們放輕鬆喝一杯，好嗎?


658
00:44:42.662 --> 00:44:46.660
My dear, how do you authors
ever think of these brilliant ideas?
親愛的，你們這些編劇
怎麼想得出這麼棒的創意?


659
00:44:46.750 --> 00:44:49.953
That damnation scene.
Did you ever in your life hear...
那場毀滅的戲，
你有沒有聽過


660
00:44:50.045 --> 00:44:54.043
My boy. I had the pleasure
of backing your last show, too.
老天，你們上一齣戲
我很開心也投資了


661
00:44:54.466 --> 00:44:55.794
Jeffrey. How about...
傑佛瑞，來個


662
00:45:12.524 --> 00:45:15.063
There it is, folks. The work light.
大夥兒，那個工作燈


663
00:45:15.152 --> 00:45:18.105
Only an electric bulb, perhaps,
but for the next four weeks...
大夥兒，那個工作燈


664
00:45:18.196 --> 00:45:21.031
that will be our sun, our moon, our stars.
會變成我們的太陽我們的月亮和星星


665
00:45:21.199 --> 00:45:24.484
These four walls will be our universe,
our private world.
這四面牆會是我們的宇宙
我們的個人世界


666
00:45:24.702 --> 00:45:27.907
We enter with nothing but a dream,
but when we leave...
我們懷抱夢想進去，
但當我們離開


667
00:45:27.998 --> 00:45:29.658
we'll have a show.
我們將會呈現一齣戲


668
00:45:29.792 --> 00:45:34.166
In between, there will be enthusiasms,
frustrations, hot tempers...
這段時間裏將有熱情、沮喪、憤怒


669
00:45:34.252 --> 00:45:35.580
cold coffee.
還有冷咖啡


670
00:45:35.670 --> 00:45:38.292
Some of us will fight, some fall in love...
有些人會吵架，有些人會相愛


671
00:45:38.381 --> 00:45:40.873
but all of us will work and adore it...
但我們大家都將會為這齣戲付出愛心…


672
00:45:40.967 --> 00:45:43.923
because all of us are inspired
by the same thing.
因為我們受到相同的啟發


673
00:45:44.013 --> 00:45:47.761
The night that curtain goes up,
it will go up on a smash hit.
當舞檯布幕升起那一晚
這齣戲將會非常轟動


674
00:45:47.975 --> 00:45:49.848
And believe me, kids...
相信我，年輕人


675
00:45:50.101 --> 00:45:53.056
there's nothing in the world as soothing...
這個世界上沒什麼比這齣戲轟動


676
00:45:53.271 --> 00:45:55.181
as a smash hit.
更叫人安慰


677
00:46:47.989 --> 00:46:51.026
What do you think this is,
summer stock or something?
你以為我們是誰?
夏天輪番上演的劇團嗎?


678
00:47:07.007 --> 00:47:09.581
POSITIVELY NO SMOKING
絕對禁煙


679
00:47:12.429 --> 00:47:13.460
Go!
開始


680
00:47:14.973 --> 00:47:19.350
That's it. That's wonderful.
Why didn't you do it before?
就是這樣，太棒了之前
為什麼不這麼樣做?


681
00:47:19.436 --> 00:47:20.894
Good, men.
做得好


682
00:47:21.061 --> 00:47:23.684
Honey, would you try
that cross, please, again for me?
親愛的，再為我走位一次好嗎


683
00:47:23.774 --> 00:47:26.941
"The same kind of opportunistic snake
that he is."
他是投機的騙子。


684
00:47:27.194 --> 00:47:29.979
"You got me wrong. I'm a self-made snake.
你搞錯了，我是自給自足的騙子


685
00:47:30.070 --> 00:47:33.439
"Listen, baby, we all live by the jungle:
Eat or be eaten.
聽著，寶貝，我們靠叢林法則生存
不是吃就是被吃…


686
00:47:33.532 --> 00:47:37.696
"I just realized that I like to eat,
and to eat caviar whenever possible.
我才明白我喜歡的魚子醬有吃時
我一定要吃~~


687
00:47:37.787 --> 00:47:39.863
"Anything wrong with that?"
這樣有錯嗎?


688
00:47:40.206 --> 00:47:42.910
"Anything wrong with that?" A bad line.
這樣有錯嗎?。這句不好


689
00:47:43.041 --> 00:47:47.618
What we need is some quick image,
like "spreading ideals on a cracker."
要能很快聯想到畫面
就像,把理想抹在餅幹上


690
00:47:47.711 --> 00:47:50.665
You all like that?
"Ever try spreading ideals on a cracker?"
你喜歡嗎?
有沒有試過把理想塗在餅幹上?


691
00:47:50.756 --> 00:47:52.215
Let me hear it, Tony.
東尼，我聽聽看


692
00:47:52.299 --> 00:47:54.707
Did you ever try spreading ideals
on a cracker?
你有沒有試過把理想塗在餅幹上?


693
00:47:54.802 --> 00:47:57.673
- Jeff. I don't...
- Honey, just try that cross again for me.
傑夫，我不…
親愛的，再為我走位一次


694
00:47:57.763 --> 00:48:00.931
"The same kind of opportunistic snake
that he is."
他是投機的騙子。


695
00:48:01.560 --> 00:48:04.228
"You got me wrong. I'm a self-made snake.
你搞錯了，我是自給自足的騙子


696
00:48:04.311 --> 00:48:07.146
"Listen, baby.
We all live by the law of the jungle..."
聽著，寶貝我們靠叢林法則生存…。


697
00:48:07.231 --> 00:48:09.140
- Excuse me, Tony.
- "...eat or be eaten."
東尼，對不起
吃或被吃。


698
00:48:09.233 --> 00:48:10.858
Pardon me, folks.
大夥兒，失陪


699
00:48:17.951 --> 00:48:19.739
You know about icebergs, don't you?
你知道冰山，不是嗎？


700
00:48:19.825 --> 00:48:22.779
One-eighth above the surface,
seven-eighths below. That's you.
八分之一浮在水面，其它都藏在水裏
你就是這樣


701
00:48:22.869 --> 00:48:25.870
You're giving me only that one-eighth.
I'm greedy. I want more.
你只給我八分之一，
我很貪心我要更多


702
00:48:25.955 --> 00:48:27.748
All eight-eighths. Now let it rip, Tony.
我要全部，東尼，放手演


703
00:48:27.833 --> 00:48:31.961
Give it too much. Go way over.
Come along. The whole eight-eighths!
誇張到極點，
再來一次，我要全部


704
00:48:32.254 --> 00:48:33.629
Okay, Gaby. Same place.
蓋比，再來一次


705
00:48:33.713 --> 00:48:35.955
"The same kind of opportunistic snake
that he is."
他是投機的騙子。


706
00:48:36.049 --> 00:48:38.088
You got me wrong. I'm a self-made snake!
你搞錯了，我是自給自足的騙子!


707
00:48:38.175 --> 00:48:41.426
Listen, baby. We all live by
the law of the jungle: Eat or be eaten!
聽著，寶貝，我們靠叢林法則生存
不是吃就是被吃!


708
00:48:41.512 --> 00:48:45.298
And I realized that I like to eat,
and eat caviar whenever possible.
有我喜歡吃的魚子醬時
我一定吃


709
00:48:45.393 --> 00:48:48.262
Did you ever try spreading ideals
on a cracker?
你有沒有試過把理想塗在餅乾上?


710
00:48:48.353 --> 00:48:51.140
Good boy, Tony. That's it. Eight-eighths.
東尼，很好，就是這樣，全部


711
00:49:03.575 --> 00:49:06.114
- Sorry. Butterfingers.
- No. It's not your fault, Tony.
對不起，我笨手笨腳不，
東尼，不是你的錯


712
00:49:06.203 --> 00:49:08.243
It's an awkward pattern.
I have a better idea.
是跳法不好，
我有個比較好的點子


713
00:49:08.331 --> 00:49:10.618
You hold your position right here,
and Jimmy...
你在這裏站好，
然後吉米


714
00:49:10.706 --> 00:49:14.122
suppose you pick up Gaby like that,
and put her down...
應該像這樣抱起蓋比
然後把她放下來…


715
00:49:14.210 --> 00:49:16.368
right here next to Tony?
Now you see, Tony...
就在東尼身邊?
現在東尼你看


716
00:49:16.461 --> 00:49:18.870
I'd like to practice it with her
two or three times.
我想和她多練習2、3次


717
00:49:18.965 --> 00:49:20.044
I think I could handle it.
我可以做到


718
00:49:20.133 --> 00:49:21.924
Do you mind if he tries it with Barbara?
讓他和芭芭拉練習好嗎?


719
00:49:22.010 --> 00:49:23.918
These are new toeshoes.
They're killing me.
這些是新鞋，磨得我腳好痛


720
00:49:24.011 --> 00:49:26.633
Sure. You go ahead and rest.
Barbara, come here. Try it.
好，你去休息，
芭芭拉，來，試試看


721
00:49:26.721 --> 00:49:28.844
I think this is what's throwing you off.
我想這就是你出問題的地方


722
00:49:28.932 --> 00:49:32.135
If you hold your balance so, like this,
then grab her here by the...
如果你的身體能這樣保持平衡
然後抓住她這裏…


723
00:49:32.227 --> 00:49:35.015
Paul, I think we're making a mistake here.
保羅，我想我們犯了一個錯


724
00:49:38.691 --> 00:49:40.601
I think we're wasting Tony in this scene.
我想這場戲對東尼是個浪費


725
00:49:40.694 --> 00:49:43.944
He's got the first-act finale right after this.
The damnation scene.
這個之後就是第一幕的結尾
那場毀滅的戲


726
00:49:44.030 --> 00:49:46.153
I don't want to dissipate
his impact in that.
我不想分散他在那場戲的份量


727
00:49:46.240 --> 00:49:50.534
Now, why not let him exit into the house
and watch it from his balcony?
何不讓他進屋子裏
然後從陽台往下看?


728
00:49:50.620 --> 00:49:52.162
- How'd that be?
- Wonderful idea.
那樣好嗎
好極了


729
00:49:52.247 --> 00:49:54.737
See what that would do?
Save your sock for the finale.
那樣如何?
把你的戲份都集中在結尾


730
00:49:54.832 --> 00:49:56.030
Much better that way.
那樣比較好


731
00:49:56.125 --> 00:49:58.415
Let's go back
to the beginning positions. Gaby.
蓋比，我們從頭再來


732
00:49:58.503 --> 00:50:00.493
Boys, get around up here,
and the girls, yes.
來，男生到這裏，
還有女生，對


733
00:50:00.586 --> 00:50:03.159
You were down here in the line like that.
Not too close.
你在舞群的邊線，
別太靠近


734
00:50:03.255 --> 00:50:05.082
This group's down here, you're up there.
這一群人在這裏，你在那裏


735
00:50:05.174 --> 00:50:06.918
- Let's try it this way.
- No!
我們試試看
不


736
00:50:07.009 --> 00:50:09.880
Let's not try it this way or any other way.
我們不要再試了


737
00:50:11.640 --> 00:50:15.768
I have had enough. I've had
three weeks of these lovely rehearsals...
我受夠了，我排演

738
00:50:15.852 --> 00:50:19.351
three weeks of Chinese torture.
I don't know what you're trying to do...
受了3個星期的酷刑
我不知道除了讓我像個


739
00:50:19.438 --> 00:50:22.142
except make me look like a complete fool.
A clumsy idiot.
受了3個星期的酷刑
我不知道除了讓我像個


740
00:50:22.232 --> 00:50:25.567
I've tried. For three weeks, I've tried.
I've taken everything.
受了3個星期的酷刑
我不知道除了讓我像個


741
00:50:25.653 --> 00:50:29.485
I've watched my part being changed,
my numbers being cut out day after day...
我看到自己戲份被改變
每天都刪掉我的舞曲…


742
00:50:29.573 --> 00:50:30.652
and I haven't said a word.
我看到自己戲份被改變
每天都刪掉我的舞曲…


743
00:50:30.741 --> 00:50:33.197
Got to be cooperative,
think of the good of the show.
盡量配合，
為這齣戲著想


744
00:50:33.285 --> 00:50:35.242
Let's get this straight:
讓我們把話說清楚


745
00:50:35.620 --> 00:50:39.202
I am not Nijinsky. I am not Marlon Brando.
我不是尼金斯基，我不是馬龍白蘭度


746
00:50:39.415 --> 00:50:42.831
I am Mrs. Hunter's little boy, Tony,
song-and-dance man.
我是杭特太太的兒子，東尼
會唱歌跳舞的傢夥


747
00:50:42.919 --> 00:50:45.954
I'm supposed to have entertained
millions of people in my time.
當紅時，我的表演
取悅無數觀眾


748
00:50:46.046 --> 00:50:50.873
And I am not entertained by
this little ballerina's snide insinuations...
現在這個小芭蕾舞者
惡意諷刺我不會跳舞．


749
00:50:50.967 --> 00:50:52.841
that I am a no-talent hoofer.
我可嚥不下這口氯


750
00:50:52.927 --> 00:50:55.964
I am sick of her superior smirk.
I'm sick of her.
我受夠了她優越的虛偽笑容
我受夠她了


751
00:50:56.056 --> 00:51:00.006
<i>I'm sick of Faust. I am sick of this show.
Never mind saying it!</i>
我受夠了《浮士德》，受夠了這齣戲
不用再說!


752
00:51:00.102 --> 00:51:02.890
Tony Hunter, 1953.
東尼杭特，l953年東山再起


753
00:51:03.356 --> 00:51:05.728
I hereby declare my independence.
我跟你們劃清界線


754
00:51:05.941 --> 00:51:09.143
Tony Hunter, 1776.
就跟l776年美國跟英國劃清界線一樣


755
00:51:09.527 --> 00:51:10.855
Bless you.
祝你好運


756
00:51:21.080 --> 00:51:23.701
STAGE DOOR
舞台出入口


757
00:51:25.708 --> 00:51:28.496
- Lester, where are you going?
- I don't know. I was...
李斯特，你要去哪裏?
我不知道，我只是…


758
00:51:28.587 --> 00:51:32.834
What's happening to us? Let's try
to keep our heads. It's only a show.
李斯特，你要去哪裏?
我不知道，我只是…


759
00:51:32.925 --> 00:51:34.715
I know. I'm sorry, baby.
我知道，寶貝，對不起


760
00:51:34.801 --> 00:51:37.921
So am I. Let's try to be sensible about it.
我也是，我們試著講理


761
00:51:38.054 --> 00:51:41.968
- Do you think we should try to find Tony?
- I don't know. What do you think?
你覺得我們該去找東尼嗎?
我不知道，你的看法呢?


762
00:51:42.057 --> 00:51:44.346
- Maybe we should.
- But Jeff said not to.
也許我們應該
但是傑夫說不要


763
00:51:44.435 --> 00:51:47.104
And, of course,
you mustn't disobey teacher.
當然，你要聽老師的話


764
00:51:47.188 --> 00:51:50.271
Right or wrong,
someone has got to be at the helm.
不管對錯，
總要有人負責


765
00:51:50.357 --> 00:51:52.931
But to you, he's 100% right every time.
不管對錯，
總要有人負責


766
00:51:53.027 --> 00:51:56.526
If you say one more word to me
about Jeff's hypnotic influence on me...
如果你再說一次
傑夫對我有催眠般的影響力


767
00:51:56.613 --> 00:51:59.400
- I'll scream.
- He's got you so bulldozed...
我就尖叫
他把你迷住了


768
00:51:59.783 --> 00:52:01.740
Someone's liable to think we're quarrelling.
有人會以為我們在吵架


769
00:52:01.826 --> 00:52:04.114
We're not quarrelling.
We're in complete agreement.
我們不是在吵架
我們完全同意彼此的看法


770
00:52:04.203 --> 00:52:05.947
We hate each other.
我們恨透對方


771
00:52:11.961 --> 00:52:13.919
WE NEVER CLOSE - Cocktails
我們從不打烊
雞尾酒


772
00:52:16.631 --> 00:52:20.843
Joe, tell Mrs. Marton I've gone to Tahiti...
喬，告訴莫頓太太我要到大溪地


773
00:52:21.428 --> 00:52:22.673
to paint.
去畫畫


774
00:52:47.912 --> 00:52:49.488
UNBREAKABLE
牢不可破


775
00:52:56.795 --> 00:53:00.211
- Hello, Mr. Hunter.
- You must have the wrong apartment.
嗨，杭特先生
你一定走錯地方了


776
00:53:00.299 --> 00:53:03.464
No. I came to see you.
May I come in a minute?
不，我是來找你，
我能進來一下嗎


777
00:53:03.676 --> 00:53:04.839
Please.
請進


778
00:53:06.261 --> 00:53:09.962
I was just about to slip
into my bed of nails.
我正準備要上床前作禱告


779
00:53:16.105 --> 00:53:17.516
I'm terribly sorry.
真是對不起


780
00:53:17.607 --> 00:53:21.652
That's all right. You couldn't have done it
if I hadn't softened it up for you.
沒關係，如果我沒先下手
你也破不壞它


781
00:53:21.736 --> 00:53:23.228
- What?
- Nothing.
什麼
沒什麼


782
00:53:24.195 --> 00:53:25.689
- Cigarette?
- No, thanks.
抽煙？
不 謝謝


783
00:53:25.780 --> 00:53:28.022
That's right. Dancers shouldn't smoke.
對，舞者不抽煙的


784
00:53:28.116 --> 00:53:31.033
- You mind if I do?
- Yes. I mean, it's all right.
如果我抽你介意嗎?
當然，我是說沒關係


785
00:53:31.118 --> 00:53:32.316
Thanks.
謝謝


786
00:53:36.208 --> 00:53:37.535
How lovely.
真漂亮


787
00:53:38.543 --> 00:53:41.578
I've never seen such wonderful prints
in a hotel.
我在旅館房間
沒看過這麼漂亮的畫


788
00:53:41.670 --> 00:53:45.714
They don't belong to the hotel yet.
They're mine, and they're originals.
這些畫不是旅館的，
是我的 他們是原作


789
00:53:46.132 --> 00:53:47.377
Don't let that throw you.
別被嚇壞了


790
00:53:47.467 --> 00:53:51.548
I don't know any more about art than I do
about dancing. I'm just a Hollywood actor.
我對藝術品的瞭解跟對舞蹈一樣有限
我不過是好萊塢的演員


791
00:53:51.639 --> 00:53:53.963
I call my agent and say,
"I've got a wall to cover.
我打電話給經紀人說
我要裝飾一面牆


792
00:53:54.057 --> 00:53:57.556
"Send me over 20 feet's worth of paintings
in assorted colours."
送一些6公尺的畫過來
各種顏色都要有。


793
00:53:59.269 --> 00:54:01.808
That's a very early Degas, isn't it?
這是很早期寶加的作品，不是嗎?


794
00:54:02.816 --> 00:54:04.643
"1877."
這是很早期寶加的作品，不是嗎?


795
00:54:06.403 --> 00:54:10.151
Yeah. I swiped it from his desk in school.
Was he sore.
對，我從他學校的桌子上
偷來的他很生氣


796
00:54:13.408 --> 00:54:14.737
What can I do for you?
你要幹嘛?


797
00:54:14.826 --> 00:54:18.243
I know. You demand an apology.
Okay, let's cut it short. I apologize.
我知道，我應該道歉好，
我們長話短說，對不起


798
00:54:18.330 --> 00:54:21.449
No, don't do that.
I'm supposed to apologize to you.
不，不要這樣，
該道歉的是我


799
00:54:22.042 --> 00:54:23.240
I mean...
我說的是真的


800
00:54:23.335 --> 00:54:26.122
I see, the fellows got together,
stuck a gun in your back...
大夥兒聚在一起，
用槍指著你


801
00:54:26.213 --> 00:54:29.331
No, it was all my idea.
I just wanted to tell you that...
不，是我自己要來的
我只是想告訴你…


802
00:54:29.422 --> 00:54:31.629
All right. It was Paul's idea.
好吧，是保羅叫我來的


803
00:54:31.758 --> 00:54:33.668
Why do I let him push me around?
為什麼他說什麼我都要聽?


804
00:54:33.760 --> 00:54:36.464
What do I want to apologize
to you for anyway?
我幹嘛跟你道歉?


805
00:54:36.554 --> 00:54:38.428
You've been mean to me.
你對我很不好


806
00:54:38.514 --> 00:54:41.886
You didn't want me in the show
in the first place.
你一開始就不希望我參與演出


807
00:54:41.978 --> 00:54:43.092
What?
什麼


808
00:54:43.187 --> 00:54:45.891
And you think
I'm a dime-a-dozen ballet dancer.
你以為我
不過是個跳芭蕾舞的


809
00:54:45.981 --> 00:54:47.012
No.
不


810
00:54:47.107 --> 00:54:50.641
And this whole thing's making me
a nervous wreck and no show is worth it.
這整件事讓我精神崩潰
戲再好都不值得


811
00:54:50.735 --> 00:54:53.856
I wouldn't apologize to you
in a million years.
就算再過l百萬年
我都不會跟你道歉


812
00:54:53.948 --> 00:54:58.075
Now, don't do that. Please, just
calm down. Now take it easy. Look.
不要這樣，拜託，
冷靜下來，放輕鬆


813
00:54:58.285 --> 00:55:00.954
I thought I was the only nervous wreck
around here...
我以為唯一精神崩潰的人是我


814
00:55:01.038 --> 00:55:02.945
and all this time you've been behaving...
這段時間以來你


815
00:55:03.038 --> 00:55:05.790
I've behaved horribly to you, and I know it.
我對你很不友善，我知道


816
00:55:05.874 --> 00:55:09.742
I'm not used to behaving horribly.
It's a big strain.
我不是這樣的人，很傷神


817
00:55:10.754 --> 00:55:14.205
You just misunderstood me, that's all.
I think you're terrific.
你誤會我了，
我覺得你很棒


818
00:55:14.299 --> 00:55:17.964
I think everything in the show
is probably terrific, except me.
我想整齣戲都很棒，除了我


819
00:55:18.053 --> 00:55:20.377
I've been scared to death of you...
我怕死你了


820
00:55:20.471 --> 00:55:23.757
and scared to death
of every last kid in the chorus.
而且怕死舞群裏的每個年輕人


821
00:55:26.978 --> 00:55:28.805
Don't be nice to me.
別說好話給我聽


822
00:55:29.898 --> 00:55:32.935
It just makes me seem twice as ugly.
只會讓我覺得自己加倍醜陋


823
00:55:36.319 --> 00:55:39.854
I'd say you were more plain than ugly...
你素淨但不醜


824
00:55:40.198 --> 00:55:42.902
- but at least you've got talent.
- Thanks.
至少你有天份
謝謝


825
00:55:43.659 --> 00:55:45.902
Now look, Gaby. It's just plain silly...
蓋比，聽著，這真的很蠢!


826
00:55:45.996 --> 00:55:48.321
that we have never sat down
and talked this out.
我們從來沒有坐下來談清楚


827
00:55:48.414 --> 00:55:51.700
We are the only animals given
the greatest means of communication...
動物中人類擁有最好的溝通資產


828
00:55:51.793 --> 00:55:52.872
human speech.
語言能力


829
00:55:52.961 --> 00:55:56.293
- And all we do is snarl at each other.
- I know.
而我們卻互相咆哮
我知道


830
00:55:56.379 --> 00:55:59.335
We're from two different worlds,
two eras...
我們來自兩個不同的世界兩個年代…


831
00:55:59.425 --> 00:56:02.510
but yet we're supposed
to dance together, work together.
但我們卻要一起跳舞，一起合作


832
00:56:02.595 --> 00:56:04.254
No one consulted us...
沒有人問過我們的意見


833
00:56:04.346 --> 00:56:07.513
but we're the only things that matter
in this whole thing.
但這整件事
少不了的是我們兩個


834
00:56:07.850 --> 00:56:11.183
Not those geniuses out there,
telling us what to do.
而不是那些告訴我們
該怎麼做的天才


835
00:56:11.686 --> 00:56:15.186
You're right.
We have to do the performing.
你是對的，
表演的人是我們


836
00:56:15.732 --> 00:56:18.269
We're the ones
that have to get up on that stage...
是我們
要站在舞台土


837
00:56:18.359 --> 00:56:22.773
- and make idiots out of ourselves.
- Tony, is that what's going to happen?
把自己弄得像個白癡
東尼，事情會變成那樣嗎?


838
00:56:22.948 --> 00:56:26.032
No. Of course not.
Things are going to be fine.
不，當然不會，
一切都會很順利


839
00:56:26.117 --> 00:56:29.651
I have a feeling that everything
is going to be much better from now on.
我覺得從現在起
一切會更順利


840
00:56:29.745 --> 00:56:31.489
Yes, I know, but...
對，我知道，但是


841
00:56:33.206 --> 00:56:35.745
Can you and I really dance together?
對，我知道，但是


842
00:56:36.628 --> 00:56:38.086
I don't know.
我不知道


843
00:56:39.213 --> 00:56:40.707
Let's find out.
我們試試看


844
00:56:46.051 --> 00:56:48.008
- Taxi, sir?
- Yes, please.
先生，計程車?
是的，麻煩你


845
00:56:53.684 --> 00:56:55.642
- El Morocco, please.
- No.
麻煩到艾爾摩洛哥
是的，麻煩你


846
00:56:56.354 --> 00:56:57.552
Stork? Waldorf?
史托克?沃朵夫?


847
00:56:57.647 --> 00:57:00.269
No. I'm not dressed.
I just came from rehearsal.
不，我沒有好好打扮
我排演完直接過來


848
00:57:00.357 --> 00:57:03.193
- I can't go to any of those places.
- You look fine to me.
那些地方我都不能去
我覺得你看起來很好


849
00:57:03.277 --> 00:57:05.519
- Never mind. Thanks.
- Thank you.
不用了，謝謝
謝謝


850
00:57:11.243 --> 00:57:14.245
- Where to, sir?
- Leave it to the horse.
先生，上哪兒?
讓馬決定


851
00:57:23.962 --> 00:57:25.753
Look, trees.
看，樹


852
00:57:26.465 --> 00:57:29.420
Yes, I remember now, dimly. Trees.
對，我隱約記起來了，樹


853
00:57:30.385 --> 00:57:32.509
And isn't that called grass?
那是不是叫草?


854
00:57:33.389 --> 00:57:35.427
And, look, there's the sky.
而且，你看，還有的天空。


855
00:57:36.266 --> 00:57:37.807
This has all been here...
當我們被困在


856
00:57:37.891 --> 00:57:41.393
the whole time we have been
shut up in our little sweatbox of the arts.
藝術的小圈圈時，它們都在這裏


857
00:57:41.481 --> 00:57:43.272
Really? Amazing.
真的?不可思議


858
00:57:43.733 --> 00:57:47.018
Do you know what those are
on those benches? People.
你知道在長椅上的是什麼?人


859
00:57:47.361 --> 00:57:48.524
Happy people.
你知道在長椅上的是什麼?人


860
00:57:48.612 --> 00:57:50.652
Would you believe it?
They don't even care...
你相信嗎?他們甚至不在乎


861
00:57:50.737 --> 00:57:54.071
whether we have a damnation scene
in our show or not.
我們有沒有演毀滅那場戲


862
00:57:55.576 --> 00:57:57.035
Neither do I.
我也不在乎


863
01:02:33.087 --> 01:02:36.871
New Haven THEATRICAL TRANSPORT CO.
New Haven, Conn.
新漢文劇院運輸公司
康乃迪克，新康恩公司


864
01:02:37.883 --> 01:02:39.959
NEW HAVEN THEATRE - STAGE ENTRANCE
新漢文劇場—舞台出入口


865
01:02:41.178 --> 01:02:43.051
You can't get it into the elevators.
這個進不了升降梯


866
01:02:43.138 --> 01:02:46.673
And you take this one here,
and it won't fit the finale.
這邊這樣，和結尾不合


867
01:02:46.808 --> 01:02:49.347
- How are we doing?
- It's a disaster.
我們進行得如何?
一團糟


868
01:02:49.436 --> 01:02:52.521
We're in terrible trouble.
We just can't open in three days.
我們麻煩大了，

869
01:02:52.606 --> 01:02:56.270
I told you from the beginning,
you are overloading the show.
我一開始就告訴你
這齣戲的東西太多了


870
01:02:56.358 --> 01:02:58.731
You can't get all this scenery
in the theatre.
這些佈景塞不進這個戲院


871
01:02:58.819 --> 01:03:01.773
- Why isn't this hung?
- We've been hanging all night.
這個怎麼還沒佈置?
我們佈置了一個晚上了


872
01:03:01.865 --> 01:03:04.320
You've got more scenery in this show...
這齣戲的佈景


873
01:03:04.409 --> 01:03:06.615
than there is in Yellowstone National Park.
多過黃石公園的景觀


874
01:03:06.703 --> 01:03:09.573
Never mind. Get your blueprints.
We'll go have a conference.
沒關係，把藍圖拿來，
我們開個會


875
01:03:09.664 --> 01:03:12.118
Everything will work out all right.
沒關係，把藍圖拿來，
我們開個會


876
01:03:17.004 --> 01:03:20.337
Hold it. I scored for brass,
and all I hear is flute.
等等，這裏是銅管樂器
我卻只聽到長笛


877
01:03:20.424 --> 01:03:22.132
I don't want so many long bows.
我不要這麼多絃樂器的聲音


878
01:03:22.217 --> 01:03:25.218
Lester, I gotta cut 16 bars
out of that dance.
李斯特，那場舞
我要刪掉l6小節的音樂


879
01:03:25.803 --> 01:03:27.676
Sixteen bars! Hey, Lil.
l6小節!嘿，莉莉


880
01:03:28.222 --> 01:03:31.092
All right, I'll make the cut. Page to page.
好，我刪，一頁一頁刪


881
01:03:31.183 --> 01:03:33.673
Would you ask Lily
if she approves the cut?
問莉莉同意嗎?


882
01:03:33.768 --> 01:03:36.141
- Lil, how about this cut?
- It's fine.
莉莉，刪掉這個好嗎?
沒關係


883
01:03:36.229 --> 01:03:37.974
Okay, Lester. Let's give it to her.
好，李斯特，給她


884
01:03:38.066 --> 01:03:41.351
This'll sound like hash.
I better put some chords in for transition.
這樣聽起來會很亂
我最好為轉場加點和弦


885
01:03:41.444 --> 01:03:44.729
Wait, just a minute.
Sublime, time, dime, slime...
等等，頂點、時間、金錢、拐騙·


886
01:03:44.822 --> 01:03:46.945
<i>You can't hear Tony in Lovelier Than You.</i>
《比你還可愛》裏聽不到東尼的聲音


887
01:03:47.031 --> 01:03:50.650
- I'm already holding down the orchestra.
- Maybe the key's too low.
《比你還可愛》裏聽不到東尼的聲音


888
01:03:51.369 --> 01:03:53.696
Ask Lester if Tony can take it a key higher.
問李斯特高一度音東尼能不能唱


889
01:03:53.790 --> 01:03:55.781
<i>About Lovelier Than You,
Les, a key higher?</i>
李斯，《比你還可愛》
高一度行嗎?


890
01:03:55.874 --> 01:03:58.579
Don't you see I'm trying to make a cut?
The key's perfect.
李斯，《比你還可愛》
高一度行嗎?


891
01:03:58.669 --> 01:04:02.035
- But Lily said you'd make the change.
- The key is...
但是莉莉說你可以改
音高是…


892
01:04:05.423 --> 01:04:08.129
<i>Everyone on their toes
for the transformation scene.</i>
每個人都在他們的位置
開始轉場的戲


893
01:04:08.219 --> 01:04:11.005
<i>- We're not ready.
- Perfectly all right. Next.</i>
我們還沒準備好
非常好，下一個


894
01:04:11.096 --> 01:04:13.254
<i>Watch it.
I'll cue you for the transition music.</i>
注意，我會告訴你何時下轉場音樂


895
01:04:13.348 --> 01:04:15.056
<i>Isn't it great? Herman.</i>
赫門，這是不是很棒?


896
01:04:15.142 --> 01:04:17.015
<i>Everybody ready back there?</i>
赫門，這是不是很棒?


897
01:04:17.100 --> 01:04:19.260
We got to have more time
to make the change.
赫門，這是不是很棒?


898
01:04:19.354 --> 01:04:22.604
- I've got to have 16 more men.
- I got elevators...
找還需要l6個人
我要升降梯…


899
01:04:22.692 --> 01:04:24.101
Do the best you can.
好，大夥兒，就是這樣


900
01:04:24.192 --> 01:04:25.984
<i>All right, everybody. This is it.</i>
大家注意。就這樣子


901
01:04:26.069 --> 01:04:28.904
<i>Men in the elevators,
watch the signal lights for your cues.</i>
大家注意。就這樣子


902
01:04:28.989 --> 01:04:32.156
<i>Switchboards. Stand by to come down
your number one batten on cue.</i>
燈光師待命。
注意你頭號板條上的提示


903
01:04:32.242 --> 01:04:35.195
<i>Girls on stairs, take your positions,
but don't be frightened.</i>
交換機待命。
注意你頭號板條上的提示


904
01:04:35.285 --> 01:04:37.574
<i>Men in armour, light your chandeliers.</i>
男生穿好盔甲，點亮吊燈


905
01:04:37.663 --> 01:04:41.909
<i>All right, make this great, everybody.
Don't forget, it's the first-act finale.</i>
好，大夥兒，好好來一次別忘了，
這是第一幕的結尾


906
01:04:43.543 --> 01:04:46.248
Are you guys all right in there?
Now, watch your cue.
你們在裏面還好嗎?
現在注意你們何時開始


907
01:04:47.506 --> 01:04:48.965
<i>Light change.</i>
改變燈光


908
01:04:49.049 --> 01:04:50.247
<i>Revolve.</i>
旋轉


909
01:04:54.887 --> 01:04:57.129
<i>This is going to be beautiful.</i>
會很美


910
01:04:57.556 --> 01:05:00.094
<i>It will be a memorable moment.</i>
會成為難忘的一刻


911
01:05:00.476 --> 01:05:01.804
<i>Memorable.</i>
難忘阿


912
01:05:03.896 --> 01:05:05.889
<i>This is real theatre.</i>
這才是戲劇


913
01:05:05.982 --> 01:05:09.515
<i>Everything's smooth as silk.</i>
每件事都非常順利


914
01:05:12.154 --> 01:05:16.815
<i>No, Herman, that doesn't go up,
it goes down. Take it down.</i>
不，赫門，那個不要上去
要下來，弄下來


915
01:05:17.659 --> 01:05:19.616
<i>What is this? Herman!</i>
赫門!這是怎麼回事?


916
01:05:20.287 --> 01:05:22.955
<i>I don't think you've got your cues right!</i>
還沒輪到你!


917
01:05:23.080 --> 01:05:24.658
<i>No, stop!</i>
不!停!


918
01:05:25.166 --> 01:05:29.293
<i>That one doesn't go down, it goes up.
Take it up.</i>
那個不要下來，要上去，
弄上去


919
01:05:30.671 --> 01:05:33.589
<i>For heaven's sake, look at your cue sheet.</i>
老天，注意看什麼時候輪到你


920
01:05:35.760 --> 01:05:39.923
<i>Take it up. No, not me.</i>
弄上去，不，不是我


921
01:05:40.890 --> 01:05:43.924
<i>Herman, this cable has fouled.</i>
赫門，鋼絲纏在一起了


922
01:05:57.946 --> 01:05:59.820
Calm down. Don't let us lose our heads.
冷靜，別失去理智


923
01:05:59.906 --> 01:06:02.695
This is a setback,
but that's what we come out of town for.
這會影響進度
所以我們才到這裏演出


924
01:06:02.785 --> 01:06:03.948
We'll never make it work.
我們完了


925
01:06:04.037 --> 01:06:07.452
Of course it will. You boys get together,
think of something brilliant.
我們沒事，你們一起想想
有沒有好辦法


926
01:06:07.540 --> 01:06:10.790
You can't put Gaby on that thing.
It's dangerous. I won't allow it.
我們沒事，你們一起想想
有沒有好辦法


927
01:06:10.876 --> 01:06:13.912
It's all right. After all, we expected
to strike a snag or two.
好，我們知道
會碰上一、兩個困難


928
01:06:14.004 --> 01:06:16.874
Get the full company in the lounge
for dialogue rehearsal...
把大家叫到休息室
當他們清理舞台時


929
01:06:16.964 --> 01:06:20.629
while they're clearing the stage.
We can't afford to waste a moment.
我們要進行對話排演
我們一刻都不能浪費


930
01:06:38.527 --> 01:06:41.197
Here. I'm sorry. I forgot.
來，對不起，我忘了


931
01:06:47.578 --> 01:06:49.034
That help?
有幫助嗎?


932
01:06:49.953 --> 01:06:51.447
All right?
這樣好嗎?


933
01:06:54.792 --> 01:06:56.831
If you've quite finished, let's try this.
這樣好嗎?


934
01:06:56.919 --> 01:06:59.588
We're going to get the stage soon.
You don't know it yet.
我們快開演了，
你們還不熟


935
01:06:59.672 --> 01:07:04.380
Paul, I'm afraid Gaby's kind of beat.
Nobody's had any sleep for two nights.
保羅，蓋比恐怕有點累了
大家已經2天沒睡了


936
01:07:04.551 --> 01:07:05.925
Can't you let her rest a while?
讓她休息一下吧?


937
01:07:06.051 --> 01:07:08.923
If you don't mind, Tony,
I've worked with her for many years.
東尼，如果你不介意
我和她合作了很多年


938
01:07:09.014 --> 01:07:11.421
I happen to know her a good deal
better than you do.
我比你還瞭解她


939
01:07:11.516 --> 01:07:12.844
All right, Gaby. Come on.
好，蓋比，來吧


940
01:07:12.934 --> 01:07:14.558
Madame, may I have this dance?
女士，能請你跳支舞嗎?


941
01:07:14.644 --> 01:07:17.727
Cut the clowning. It's not going to seem
so funny tomorrow night.
別鬧了，明天晚上
可就不會這麼好玩了


942
01:07:17.813 --> 01:07:19.188
All right, Adam.
好 亞當


943
01:07:28.532 --> 01:07:32.066
Okay, Paul, they're ready for you on-stage.
Come on.
好，保羅，他們在舞台上等你，
來


944
01:07:37.083 --> 01:07:40.948
This is the big moment.
Hal, come on. Take it over there.
這是重要的一刻，
來哈爾，拿到那邊去


945
01:07:41.043 --> 01:07:45.125
Tony, Gaby, this is it.
I want it to be outstanding.
東尼、蓋比，就是這一刻
我希望有傑出的表現


946
01:07:45.507 --> 01:07:50.632
It must be beautiful, fabulous,
warm, and fiery.
一定要優美、不凡、溫暖而且熱情


947
01:07:54.056 --> 01:07:57.055
Your cue is, "Dance, fools, dance!"
唱到"跳吧，白癡們跳吧!"時你們就開始


948
01:08:56.324 --> 01:09:00.237
Hal, it seems to be a little too much,
doesn't it?
哈爾，似乎太多了點，
不是嗎


949
01:09:01.412 --> 01:09:02.656
Yes.
是


950
01:09:04.664 --> 01:09:07.664
Are we really supposed
to open tomorrow night?
明天晚上
真的是我們的首演?


951
01:09:13.214 --> 01:09:15.503
"Dance, fools, dance!"
跳吧，白癡們跳吧!


952
01:09:25.892 --> 01:09:28.810
The New Haven Theatre PRESENTS THE
新漢文劇場推出


953
01:09:28.895 --> 01:09:31.813
JEFFREY CORDOVA PRODUCTION OF
The Band Wagon
傑佛瑞可多瓦製作的
龍鳳花車


954
01:09:31.899 --> 01:09:33.607
OPENING TONIGHT
NEW GREAT MUSICAL
今晚首演最精采的
新音樂劇


955
01:09:33.692 --> 01:09:36.525
ALL OF THE NATION'S GREATEST HITS
轟動全國


956
01:09:37.778 --> 01:09:40.483
Hello, there! It's a big night.
嗨，今晚真盛大!


957
01:09:42.741 --> 01:09:46.111
Everybody is here from New York.
Simply everybody.
紐約客都來了，
大家都來了


958
01:09:46.204 --> 01:09:49.158
Do you hear that, my dear?
Everybody from New York is here.
親愛的，聽到了嗎?
紐約客都到這裏來了


959
01:09:50.040 --> 01:09:52.745
Come on. Don't want you
to miss the overture.
來，可不希望錯過開場


960
01:09:53.668 --> 01:09:55.578
Think we should get ready, boys?
我們應該動手了嗎?


961
01:09:55.671 --> 01:09:58.873
No, we can finish this hand.
Nobody's made a pep talk yet.
不，把這一局玩完，
還沒精神講話呢


962
01:09:59.341 --> 01:10:00.420
Pep talk?
精神講話?


963
01:10:01.009 --> 01:10:03.880
Yeah. I never seen an opening night yet
without some guy...
對，首演當晚不是都會有一個人


964
01:10:03.971 --> 01:10:07.671
gets all the poor actors together
and makes them a long speech:
把所有可憐的演員集合起來
來一段精神講話…


965
01:10:07.766 --> 01:10:09.510
"They should be brilliant."
把所有可憐的演員集合起來
來一段精神講話…


966
01:10:09.850 --> 01:10:12.340
On-stage, please. Everybody on-stage.
拜託大家都到舞台土


967
01:10:14.812 --> 01:10:16.770
Mr. Cordova wants to say a few words.
可多瓦先生有幾句話要說


968
01:10:16.856 --> 01:10:20.225
Come on, girls. Hurry up. Let's go.
Step right along.
女生動作快，來，
站在一起


969
01:10:26.657 --> 01:10:30.525
Company, a final word.
You've all been just wonderful.
大夥兒，最後幾句話
這段時間你們都很棒


970
01:10:30.703 --> 01:10:32.281
Thanks for your cooperation.
謝謝你們的合作


971
01:10:32.373 --> 01:10:35.456
Tonight, we're about to perform
before an audience in a theatre.
今晚，我們要在劇場
公開首演


972
01:10:35.542 --> 01:10:38.377
It's not only a temple of the arts,
but a place of business.
劇場不只是藝術殿堂
也是生意場所


973
01:10:38.462 --> 01:10:41.746
And I feel we have here a venture
that is successful on both counts.
我們在兩邊的表現
都很成功


974
01:10:41.839 --> 01:10:45.208
Nothing to be nervous about.
We've got to keep our wits and do a show.
沒什麼好擔心的，
我們要冷靜地演出


975
01:10:45.300 --> 01:10:47.792
There will be rough spots,
but we'll smooth them out.
會有不匱的地方，
但我們會克服


976
01:10:47.886 --> 01:10:50.424
Remember, that's what
we came out of town for.
記住，這就是我們
到這裏演出的原因


977
01:10:50.513 --> 01:10:53.467
Up to now,
I've been giving you orders as director...
現在，
我以導演的身份給你們指示…


978
01:10:54.059 --> 01:10:57.557
but when next you see me,
I shall be just as one of you...
但等一下你們看到我時
我就跟你們任何人一樣．


979
01:10:57.645 --> 01:11:00.432
an eager ham, anxious to make good.
是熱切的演員，焦慮地希望有好表現


980
01:11:01.023 --> 01:11:03.858
Actors, let's go.
演員們 上吧


981
01:11:04.026 --> 01:11:06.518
All right, people.
Get ready for the tableau, girls.
好，大夥兒，
準備上戲吧


982
01:11:06.613 --> 01:11:09.234
Finish your make-up.
Come on, girls. Let's go.
把妝化完，快，
女生，走吧


983
01:11:10.951 --> 01:11:12.908
I'm so glad you folks could come.
真高興你們能來


984
01:11:13.036 --> 01:11:16.073
And don't forget the big party
at the hotel after the show.
別忘了散場後
飯店有一個盛大的派對


985
01:11:16.165 --> 01:11:18.487
The whole cast will be there.
You'll meet them all.
全部的演員都會到場
你會見到每一個人


986
01:11:18.581 --> 01:11:22.661
Of course, I have to go backstage
to congratulate them afterwards.
當然，散場後我要到後台恭喜他們


987
01:11:22.835 --> 01:11:25.042
I'll see you all at the party.
派對上再見


988
01:11:25.505 --> 01:11:27.296
All New York is here.
整個紐約都來了


989
01:11:28.216 --> 01:11:30.209
Big party at the hotel after the show.
散場後飯店有一個盛大的派對


990
01:11:30.302 --> 01:11:33.670
I'll look for you. Big party, big show.
Come on, now.
希望見到你，盛大派對
盛大演出，走吧


991
01:11:35.722 --> 01:11:38.759
We don't want to miss a thing.
Now, don't forget the party.
我們什麼都不想錯過
別忘了還有派對


992
01:11:38.851 --> 01:11:42.551
Evelyn, big party at the hotel
after the show.
艾芙琳，散場後飯店有盛大派對


993
01:11:42.646 --> 01:11:44.271
I'll look for you.
希望見到妳


994
01:11:45.733 --> 01:11:47.392
Champagne's on me.
香檳我請客


995
01:11:49.194 --> 01:11:53.689
The Band Wagon
WILL BE THE Great Hit OF THE YEAR
龍鳳花車
將是今年最轟動的大戲


996
01:12:33.444 --> 01:12:36.611
Shall I drive you to the hotel, sir,
to the party?
先生，要我載你到飯店參加派對嗎


997
01:12:38.073 --> 01:12:39.354
No. Drive me to the station.
不，載我到車站


998
01:12:39.450 --> 01:12:42.368
Maybe I can still make the 11:40
back to New York.
不，載我到車站


999
01:12:42.453 --> 01:12:43.698
Yes, sir.
是，先生


1000
01:13:15.983 --> 01:13:19.601
<i>- Good evening.
- I was looking for The Band Wagon party.</i>
你好
我來參加《龍鳳花車》的派對


1001
01:13:19.696 --> 01:13:21.274
This is it, sir.
你好
我來參加《龍鳳花車》的派對


1002
01:13:30.373 --> 01:13:33.077
<i>Let's go. Hurry up. Champagne.</i>
來吧，快，香檳


1003
01:13:39.756 --> 01:13:41.749
This way, please.
這邊請


1004
01:14:14.248 --> 01:14:17.035
- Are you leaving, sir?
- Yes. Good night.
先生，你要走了嗎?
對，再見


1005
01:14:18.877 --> 01:14:21.000
We must do this more often.
我們應該常開派對


1006
01:14:25.383 --> 01:14:30.009
<i>Oh, give me something
to remember you by</i>
哦，讓我記得你


1007
01:14:32.515 --> 01:14:37.058
<i>When you are far away from me</i>
當你離我遠去


1008
01:14:39.896 --> 01:14:41.935
<i>Some little something</i>
一些小事


1009
01:14:42.022 --> 01:14:43.896
It's all Annie's fault.
都是安妮的錯


1010
01:14:45.067 --> 01:14:49.479
I should have listened to my mother.
She told me only to be in hit shows.
我應該聽我媽的話
她告訴我只參與轟動的秀


1011
01:14:51.951 --> 01:14:53.575
Hi, I don't want to barge in.
嗨，我無意闖入


1012
01:14:53.661 --> 01:14:56.232
I just want to tell you all
how great I think you are.
我只想說你們都很棒


1013
01:14:56.328 --> 01:14:58.285
I didn't get a chance
to know you very well.
我只想說你們都很棒


1014
01:14:58.372 --> 01:15:03.284
- I'm sorry I messed up the show for you.
- Wait a minute, come on in, have a drink.
對不起，我把這齣戲搞砸了
等等，來，喝一杯


1015
01:15:03.377 --> 01:15:06.544
- I don't want to crash the party.
- Give Mr. Hunter a drink.
我不想破壞你們的派對
給杭特先生一杯酒


1016
01:15:06.631 --> 01:15:09.335
- What do you say, Scotch, rye, or beer?
- Beer's fine.
你要什麼?威士忌、黑麥或啤酒?
啤酒好了


1017
01:15:09.425 --> 01:15:12.210
- One beer, coming up.
- Want some pizza pie?
一杯啤酒，馬上來
想要來片披薩嗎?


1018
01:15:12.301 --> 01:15:15.302
How about a sandwich?
We've got ham and devilled egg.
三明治怎麼樣?
我們有火腿和雞蛋沙拉


1019
01:15:15.387 --> 01:15:18.009
I've had enough of both for one night.
足夠我飽一個晚上。


1020
01:15:23.271 --> 01:15:27.683
<i>Far away
Me, oh, my</i>
遠離，我或我的


1021
01:15:27.774 --> 01:15:31.522
<i>Only yesterday</i>
只是昨天


1022
01:15:35.449 --> 01:15:38.449
There we were, the whole act,
the 10 Tapping Troubadours.
就是這樣，整齣戲

1023
01:15:38.535 --> 01:15:40.611
The 10 Tapping Troubadours?

1024
01:15:40.704 --> 01:15:42.116
Yeah, believe it or not...

1025
01:15:42.207 --> 01:15:44.614
we were stranded in Pittsburgh
with $3 between us...

1026
01:15:44.709 --> 01:15:47.707
crammed into one room
the size of that closet.
擠在一間跟那個衣櫥
一樣大的房間


1027
01:15:49.002 --> 01:15:52.087
Gaby, come on in.
We're having a good old-fashioned wake.
擠在一間跟那個衣櫥
一樣大的房間


1028
01:15:53.339 --> 01:15:55.167
I've been looking all over for you.
我到處找你們


1029
01:15:55.259 --> 01:15:56.338
Where is Paul?
保羅呢?


1030
01:15:56.427 --> 01:15:59.381
He's at a very exclusive wake
with Jeff and the Martons.
他和傑夫以及莫頓夫婦
也有他們自己的聚會


1031
01:15:59.472 --> 01:16:01.760
Can I get you a drink, Gaby?
How about a beer?
蓋比，要喝什麼?
啤酒怎麼樣?


1032
01:16:01.849 --> 01:16:03.721
How about some popcorn?
來點爆米花如何?


1033
01:16:06.811 --> 01:16:08.804
Lily, Lester, come on in.
莉莉、李斯特，進來


1034
01:16:09.648 --> 01:16:12.981
Are you sure? Don't you remember?
We wrote that thing.
你確定?你忘了嗎?
那齣戲是我們寫的


1035
01:16:13.068 --> 01:16:15.688
This is a wonderful party. Come on in.
你確定?你忘了嗎?
那齣戲是我們寫的


1036
01:16:16.320 --> 01:16:19.653
Who's going to go out and get the beer?
Okay, Sis, you're elected.
你確定?你忘了嗎?
那齣戲是我們寫的


1037
01:16:19.740 --> 01:16:21.650
Tony, watch this!
東尼，聽聽看這個!


1038
01:16:24.328 --> 01:16:25.739
More beer!
更多啤酒!


1039
01:16:26.872 --> 01:16:29.279
I'll never forget. You blew a gasket.
我永遠會記得，你當時很生氣


1040
01:16:29.374 --> 01:16:31.580
You were really gone. Come on.
你當時真的失控，來


1041
01:16:34.672 --> 01:16:37.671
Come on, Tony. Come on, get with it.
來，東尼，快開始


1042
01:16:37.757 --> 01:16:41.921
<i>- How I love the glass of beer
- More beer</i>
我多喜歡來杯啤酒
更多啤酒


1043
01:16:42.512 --> 01:16:47.174
<i>- Beer goes very good with beer
- More beer</i>
啤酒最好配啤酒
更多啤酒


1044
01:16:47.350 --> 01:16:52.012
<i>When I'm drinking beer I'm thinking
'"Ach, life is dear'"</i>
當我喝啤酒我覺得"哦，人生可貴"。


1045
01:16:52.146 --> 01:16:57.020
<i>But there's someone I love
even more than beer</i>
但是我有一個愛人更勝啤酒


1046
01:16:58.776 --> 01:17:03.237
<i>I love Louisa
Louisa loves me</i>
我愛露易莎 露易莎愛我


1047
01:17:03.657 --> 01:17:08.200
<i>When we rode on the merry-go-round
I kissed Louisa</i>
當我們騎旋轉木馬時我吻露易莎


1048
01:17:08.286 --> 01:17:12.367
<i>And then Louisa
Louisa kissed me</i>
露易莎吻我


1049
01:17:12.915 --> 01:17:17.376
<i>We were so happy
So happy and free</i>
我們好愉快好愉快好自在


1050
01:17:17.671 --> 01:17:22.047
<i>Ach! Ach! But she's a
beautiful Louisa</i>
我們好愉快好愉快好自在


1051
01:17:22.133 --> 01:17:26.675
<i>Ach! When I choose 'em
I never want to lose 'em</i>
啊，當我選她我就不想失去她


1052
01:17:26.762 --> 01:17:31.339
<i>Someday Louisa
Louisa will be</i>
有一天露易莎 露易莎將是


1053
01:17:31.432 --> 01:17:34.432
<i>More als just a Fräulein to me</i>
我眼中不平凡的女子


1054
01:17:38.273 --> 01:17:42.566
<i>- Frenchmen love a glass of wine
- More beer</i>
法國人喜歡來杯紅酒
更多啤酒


1055
01:17:42.652 --> 01:17:47.194
<i>- The English think the whiskey's fine
- More beer</i>
英國人喜歡威士忌
更多啤酒


1056
01:17:47.280 --> 01:17:51.695
<i>But when I comb off all the foam off
I drink a toast</i>
當我把啤酒泡泡弄掉
我一口幹掉


1057
01:17:51.911 --> 01:17:54.699
<i>To the Germans and the Mädchen</i>
敬德國姑娘


1058
01:17:54.790 --> 01:17:58.324
<i>I love most</i>
我的最愛


1059
01:17:58.501 --> 01:18:02.913
<i>Ich liebe Louisa
Louisa liebt mich</i>
我愛露易莎 露易莎愛我


1060
01:18:03.088 --> 01:18:07.880
<i>Wenn wir auf das Ringelspiel gehen
Ich küsse Louisa</i>
當我們騎旋轉木馬我吻露易莎


1061
01:18:07.967 --> 01:18:11.798
<i>Und dann Louisa
Louisa küsst mich</i>
露易莎吻我


1062
01:18:11.887 --> 01:18:16.764
<i>Wir sind so glücklich
So glücklich sind wir</i>
我們好愉快好愉快好自在


1063
01:18:16.852 --> 01:18:21.393
<i>Ach! Ach! But she's a
beautiful Louisa</i>
她是美麗的露易莎


1064
01:18:21.480 --> 01:18:26.141
<i>Ach! When I choose 'em
I never want to lose 'em</i>
啊!當我選她我就不想失去她


1065
01:18:43.793 --> 01:18:48.170
<i>Ach! Ach! But she's a
beautiful Louisa</i>
啊!啊!但是她是漂亮的露易莎


1066
01:18:48.255 --> 01:18:52.548
<i>Ach! When I choose 'em
I never want to lose 'em</i>
啊!當我選她我就不想失去她


1067
01:18:52.634 --> 01:18:56.964
<i>Someday Louisa
Louisa will be</i>
有一天露易莎露易莎會是


1068
01:18:57.055 --> 01:19:00.259
<i>More than just a Fräulein to me</i>
我眼中不凡的女子


1069
01:19:00.351 --> 01:19:04.679
<i>More beer!
More beer!</i>
更多啤酒!
更多啤酒!


1070
01:19:04.771 --> 01:19:08.471
<i>More beer!</i>
更多啤酒!


1071
01:19:24.164 --> 01:19:27.829
Gosh, with all this raw talent around,
why can't us kids get together...
老天，有這麼多才華洋溢的年輕人
我們何不聚在一起…


1072
01:19:27.918 --> 01:19:29.377
and put on ourselves a show?
製作一齣自己的秀?


1073
01:19:29.461 --> 01:19:33.245
Maybe we can find ourselves
a barn or something, and maybe...
也許我們可以找個穀倉之類的


1074
01:19:36.844 --> 01:19:39.334
I could stand anything but failure.
我就是無法接受失敗


1075
01:19:40.764 --> 01:19:43.170
- Where's the telephone?
- In there.
電話呢
在那裏


1076
01:19:50.689 --> 01:19:53.226
Give me Jeff Cordova's room, please.
幫我接傑夫可多瓦


1077
01:19:54.400 --> 01:19:57.934
Hello, Jeff. This is Tony.
Now, don't say anything. Just listen.
喂，傑夫，是我東尼什麼都不要說，
聽我說


1078
01:19:58.028 --> 01:20:00.698
I'm here with all the kids,
and we've come to a decision.
我和這些年輕演員在一起
我們做了個決定


1079
01:20:00.781 --> 01:20:04.697
We're not closing this show,
if you can call it a show. We're going on.
我和這些年輕演員在一起
我們做了個決定


1080
01:20:04.786 --> 01:20:08.202
We're going to keep it on the road
and redo it from top to bottom.
我和這些年輕演員在一起
我們做了個決定


1081
01:20:08.289 --> 01:20:10.198
<i>It won't be a modern version of Faust...</i>
不會是現代版的《浮士德》


1082
01:20:10.291 --> 01:20:12.962
<i>Pilgrim 's Progress, or the Book of Job
in swing time.</i>
《天路歷程》或是《約伯記》
的搖擺歌舞片


1083
01:20:13.045 --> 01:20:15.794
It'll be our show,
the show we started out to do...
《天路歷程》或是《約伯記》的搖擺歌舞片


1084
01:20:15.879 --> 01:20:18.548
the book the Martons wrote,
with the songs you threw out.
《天路歷程》或是《約伯記》的搖擺歌舞片


1085
01:20:18.632 --> 01:20:21.585
It'll have laughs and entertainment.
You remember entertainment?
《天路歷程》或是《約伯記》的搖擺歌舞片


1086
01:20:21.675 --> 01:20:23.715
Look, we'd love to have you with us, Jeff.
聽著，傑夫，我們希望你加入


1087
01:20:23.803 --> 01:20:25.962
But if you're not,
it won't make any difference.
如果你不想，也無所謂


1088
01:20:26.056 --> 01:20:27.550
We're going ahead just the same.
如果你不想，也無所謂


1089
01:20:27.641 --> 01:20:30.594
We're going to put this thing across,
aren't we, kids?
如果你不想，也無所謂


1090
01:20:30.685 --> 01:20:33.851
<i>- All right. What do you say?
- Hello? There's nobody here.</i>
好，你覺得怎麼樣?
喂?這裏沒有人


1091
01:20:33.938 --> 01:20:36.854
This is the chambermaid, but if you want...
我是打掃房間的，如果你要


1092
01:20:36.940 --> 01:20:40.357
<i>- I'll leave a message for Mr. Cordova.
- Thank you, madam.</i>
我可以幫可多瓦先生留話，
女士謝謝你


1093
01:20:40.903 --> 01:20:42.314
He isn't in.
他不在


1094
01:20:53.832 --> 01:20:56.240
Jeff, did you hear what I said?
傑夫，你聽到我剛剛說的嗎?


1095
01:20:57.918 --> 01:21:01.335
Tony, I've learned one thing in the theatre,
and it's this:
傑夫，你聽到我剛剛說的嗎?


1096
01:21:01.422 --> 01:21:04.708
one man has to be at the helm,
the rest take orders.
傑夫，你聽到我剛剛說的嗎?


1097
01:21:05.592 --> 01:21:09.425
I believe in what you said.
I got carried away in the wrong direction.
我相信你說的，
我走錯方向了


1098
01:21:09.513 --> 01:21:14.258
You've got to be the boss, Tony.
I think you can pull this off brilliantly...
東尼，你要負起責任
你一定可以表現得很精采


1099
01:21:15.519 --> 01:21:17.845
and I'd like to be a part of it.
我很樂意加入


1100
01:21:19.940 --> 01:21:21.103
Jeff, you're all right.
傑夫，好


1101
01:21:21.191 --> 01:21:23.431
I must tell you one thing.
There isn't any money.
有件事我一定要告訴你
一毛錢都沒有


1102
01:21:23.525 --> 01:21:26.810
Colonel Todd and the backers
have stolen away into the night.
有件事我一定要告訴你
一毛錢都沒有


1103
01:21:26.903 --> 01:21:28.018
- We've got backers.
- Who?
我們有贊助者?
誰?


1104
01:21:28.112 --> 01:21:30.320
A bunch of painters.
A fellow named Degas from...
一群畫家，
一個叫寶加來自...


1105
01:21:30.408 --> 01:21:33.445
- You wouldn't sell your paintings.
- Sure, they love the theatre.
你不是要賣那些畫吧
沒錯，它們喜歡戲劇


1106
01:21:33.537 --> 01:21:37.616
I figure we need five or six weeks on tour
to do what we have to do with this show.
我想我們這個演出
要巡迴5到6周


1107
01:21:37.707 --> 01:21:40.244
- Jeff, would you help us with bookings?
- Of course.
傑夫，你可以幫我們安排檔期嗎?
當然


1108
01:21:40.334 --> 01:21:43.668
Hal, have you got paper and pencil?
We can send a telegram.
哈爾，你有沒有紙和筆?
我們可以發一封電報


1109
01:21:46.173 --> 01:21:48.295
- Washington? Washington's open.
- And Boston.
華盛頓?華盛頓有檔期
還有波士頓


1110
01:21:48.383 --> 01:21:49.462
Boston's very good.
波士頓很好


1111
01:21:49.551 --> 01:21:52.837
Can we go to Philadelphia, Detroit,
then come on back to New York?
我們可以到費城、底特律
然後回到紐約嗎?


1112
01:21:52.930 --> 01:21:56.593
- Paul, aren't you excited?
- Yeah. It's wonderful.
保羅，你不高興嗎?
高興，太好了


1113
01:21:57.641 --> 01:21:59.634
I wish them a lot of luck.
保羅，你不高興嗎?
高興，太好了


